SYMPTOM_TEXT: I received the second dose of the COVID-19 vaccine on January 13, 2021. In early March, I began experiencing some health concerns. I have a history of Dysautonomia and Anxiety. The dysautonomia has been controlled with lifestyle modifications for over 5 years. Symptoms experienced with it include low blood pressure, tachycardia, pre syncopal feelings and syncope. The occurrence of these symptoms became more frequent after receiving my second vaccination. In addition to above symptoms, my anxiety has worsened (which has been well controlled on the same medication for over 5 years), more syncopal episodes, acute weight loss, increased fatigue, lower baseline blood pressure, hair loss, temperature instability, and intermittent chest heaviness.   In June, I had a dental procedure in which local epinephrine and lidocaine was used.  I drove myself as I was told this would not be an issue since nitrous or general anesthesia was not used. I left the appointment to drive 20 minutes home. Within 5 minutes of my house, I began with pre-syncopal feelings (dizziness, blurred vision, pounding headache). I pulled off on side of road and within seconds, I had loss consciousness. I was by myself so unsure as to how long before I regained consciousness. When I woke up, I notified  my spouse. I noted that I had loss bowel and bladder control during this episode, which has never occurred during my syncopal episodes. My foot was also cut from the foot pedals. My spouse said it took approximately 45 minutes for me to return to baseline. This episode was concerning for seizure activity, in which I will be evaluated by a Neurologist. I have no history of seizure activity. I have been evaluated per my primary and cardiologist. Cardiology believes my dysautonomia has worsened and is being exacerbated and feels as if this may have caused a rebound reaction to the local meds.   But why now? Why is my dysautonomia worsening when I'm an otherwise healthy, young adult.
LAB_DATA: Primary Provider  (June 24) - CBC w/ diff, CMP, Thyroid studies, EKG negative.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: On May 5th, 2021 at 10:45 am I experienced severe dizziness and faintness. I was unable to ride from a laying position without passing out. When I would try to sit up my heart rate would go from the low 60s to 120-130 before I would faint. This condition was persistent for 4 hours and my parents made the decision for me to go to the emergency room.  At the Er they administered fluids and observed me for about 4 hours and then sent me home because I could stand and walk. They also determined that I was somewhat anemic, my hemoglobin was 9.6.   In the weeks following these visits I had a number of episodes these episodes including symptoms of heart palpitations, tingly hands, and feet, mouth, and chin going numb,  feeling faint and dizzy eyes, and other visual disturbances. One of these episodes occurred on June 12th, 2021 while I was driving. I felt heart palpitations, tingly hands, and feet, face and chin going numb and feeling faint. I pulled over which happened to be in a parking lot where there was an Er. I went in and got evaluated. They ran an EKG but felt they did not catch whatever the episode was so they prescribed me a portable heart monitor. Which I wore for 14 days and am now waiting for the results.
LAB_DATA: On May 5th they ran blood tests and determined that my hemoglobin was low(9.6), so they prescribed 325mg of Iron daily that I have been taking.   On June 12th they took blood tests and my Iron levels were up to normal and my troponin was normal. They took an EKG, and prescribed a portable heart monitor which we are waiting for results from.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient presents in fulminant liver failure. Per GI team documentation: "We do not have an etiology for this acute liver injury.  The differential diagnosis includes drug-induced liver injury, acute viral hepatitis, ischemic hepatitis, autoimmune hepatitis and indeterminate.  Acetaminophen and salicylate levels are negative.  Alcohol level is negative.  Although patient does abuse alcohol on a daily basis, her presentation is not consistent with acute alcoholic hepatitis.  Serologies have been sent to evaluate the differential diagnosis and other potential causes of acute liver injury.  Liver imaging including Doppler ultrasound does not reveal any abnormality and there is no evidence of chronic liver disease."  We have found four case reports of hepatitis/autoimmune hepatitis related to mRNA vaccines. We have additionally had a case of fulminant liver failure in our community a few months back of which no other etiology was identified other then mRNA vaccine. Because of such, and with no other identifiable cause, we are concerned her acute sudden liver failure was vaccine induced.

The patient's height, and weight were not reported. The patient's concurrent conditions included arthritis, penicillin allergy, and allergy to wasps. The patient received covid-19 vaccine ad26.cov2.s (suspension for injection, route of admin not reported, batch number: 025A21A, expiry: UNKNOWN) dose was not reported, administered on 29-APR-2021 at right arm for prophylactic vaccination. Concomitant medications included naproxen sodium for arthritis, chlorphenamine maleate for itchy skin, cyanocobalamin, and fluticasone propionate. Patient experienced tiredness, some general malaise and slept for most of the next day of vaccination, but did not experienced other significant symptoms after the vaccination. However, on 29-JUN-2021, patient had severe allergic reaction included anaphylaxis and her hand started itching then swelling spread to the hands and face. She had put her hands under cold water and by then they were completely red, Legs then became red, then the nape of the neck began to itch, She was dripping wet with sweat at that point. She then had to immediately get to the bathroom as she voided and vomited for the next three hours. EMS was called at 10 o'clock and was taken to the hospital. At the hospital no medications were given. Vitals were fine, Blood pressure was 128/76 mmHg, pulse was 83 bpm, and oxygen saturation was 97%. Treatment medications (dates unspecified) included: epinephrine. The action taken with covid-19 vaccine ad26.cov2.s was not applicable. The patient recovered from slept for most of the next day on 30-APR-2021, and the outcome of general malaise, anaphylaxis (severe allergic reaction, itching in hand and nape of neck, voided and vomited for three hours, swelling in hands, swelling on face, red hands and leg and dripping wet with sweat) and tiredness was not reported. Allergic reaction to the vaccine; Hives on the posterior aspect of both arm and the posterior left leg; This spontaneous case was reported by a physician and describes the occurrence of ALLERGY TO VACCINE (Allergic reaction to the vaccine) and URTICARIA (Hives on the posterior aspect of both arm and the posterior left leg) in a 38-year-old female patient who received mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) for COVID-19 vaccination.     Concomitant products included BENZTROPINE [BENZATROPINE], HALOPERIDOL, METHADONE, MIRTAZAPINE and POLYETHYLENE for an unknown indication.    On 06-Feb-2021 at 11:35 AM, the patient received first dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) 1 dosage form. On 06-Feb-2021 at 1:27 PM, the patient experienced ALLERGY TO VACCINE (Allergic reaction to the vaccine) (seriousness criterion intervention required) and URTICARIA (Hives on the posterior aspect of both arm and the posterior left leg) (seriousness criterion intervention required). The patient was treated with DIPHENHYDRAMINE HYDROCHLORIDE (BENADRYL [DIPHENHYDRAMINE HYDROCHLORIDE]) (intramuscular) on 06-Feb-2021 for Adverse event, at a dose of 25 mg once a day; DIPHENHYDRAMINE HYDROCHLORIDE (BENADRYL [DIPHENHYDRAMINE HYDROCHLORIDE]) (intramuscular) on 06-Feb-2021 for Adverse event, at a dose of 50 mg once a day and PREDNISONE (oral) on 06-Feb-2021 for Adverse event, at a dose of 60 mg once a day. At the time of the report, ALLERGY TO VACCINE (Allergic reaction to the vaccine) and URTICARIA (Hives on the posterior aspect of both arm and the posterior left leg) had resolved.      DIAGNOSTIC RESULTS (normal ranges are provided in parenthesis if available): On 06-Feb-2021, Vital signs measurement: normal (normal) normal.     The action taken with mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) was unknown.   For mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular), the reporter did not provide any causality assessments.   Treatment for the event included 25mg bendaryl IM, 60mg prednisone PO. The patient was not having any breathing difficulty, lungs were clear and vitals were normal. After treatment, the patient was monitored for 30 minutes more and found that itching stopped. The patient went to UC approximately four hours later stating that her symptoms reoccurred.  Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.; Sender's Comments: Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.

This case involves a 1-years-old female patient who was vaccinated with DIPHTHERIA-15/TETANUS/5 HYBRID AC PERTUSSIS/IPV (MRC5) VACCINE [QUADRACEL] instead of DIPHTHERIA/TETANUS/5 HYBRID AC PERTUSSIS/IPV(VERO)/HIB(PRP/T) VACCINE [PENTACEL (VERO)].  The patient's medical history, medical treatments, vaccinations, concomitant medications and family history were not provided.  Concomitant medications included VARICELLA ZOSTER VACCINE (VARICELLA VACCINE), PNEUMOCOCCAL VACCINE CONJ 7V (CRM197) (PREVNAR) and MEASLES VACCINE, MUMPS VACCINE, RUBELLA VACCINE (MMR) (lot number and expiration date not reported) via unknown route and site of administration for prophylactic vaccination.  On 09-Jun-2021, the patient received a 0.5 mL dose of suspect DIPHTHERIA-15/TETANUS/5 HYBRID AC PERTUSSIS/IPV (MRC5) VACCINE (lot number : C5778BA and expiry date : 07-Oct-2022) via an intramuscular route in the left vastus lateralis for prophylactic vaccination.  It was an actual medication error case due to wrong vaccine administered (wrong product administered, latency: same day).  At the time of reporting, no adverse event was reported.  This suspected adverse reaction report is submitted and classified as a medication error solely and exclusively to ensure the marketing authorization holder's compliance with the requirements set out in Directive 2001/83/EC and Module VI of the Good Pharmacovigilance Practices. The classification as a medical error is in no way intended, nor should it be interpreted or construed as an allegation or claim made by the marketing authorization holder that any third party has contributed to or is to be held liable for the occurrence of this medication error.

Within 24 hours of getting the first vaccine dose, my ears starting ringing and a feeling of pressure increased in my head/ears to an uncomfortable amount and made it hard to concentrate and to hear.  The effect is similar to being underwater - pressure filled head and muffled hearing.  The ringing continued for about 48 hours.  The pressure effect in my ears and head continued for several days.  It has come and gone over the last several months, lasting a few days at a time then waning for a few days before coming back and sometimes comes with mild pain in ears.  I thought it was possibly a new reaction to seasonal allergies that I just have never have experienced and started taking decongestant.  It gave a little relief however inconsistently.  I asked my primary care doctor at my annual appointment about it and she referred me to an ENT. Completed a physical exam and his office completed an audiology and pressure test.  Pressure in the ears was normal, however the audiology test showed hearing loss in my right ear.  Said that sudden hearing loss was likely due to a virus and pressure feeling came along with hearing loss.  The ear pain may be related to teeth grinding.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 5/9 PM: heart palpitations, chest pressure and left chest pains developed. BP went up to 140/99 and stayed high, heart rate normal, had loose stool/diarrhea throughout evening. Difficulty sleeping because of discomfort and anxiety over discomfort. First day of my placebo week for hormonal birth control. 5/10: Loose stool, pressure and discomfort continued throughout day, sore arm/armpit, shortness of breath when doing simple daily tasks (walking around apartment, going up a flight of stairs). Very fatigued, low energy, low appetite. 5/11: Headache developed, BP 132/98, had telehealth appt with PCP and was advised to admit myself to emergency room. All tests came back normal, I was told that ER doctor had seen 30-40 patients who felt very ill after second vaccine but that over a week they started to feel better. - continued feeling symptoms throughout week, slept 18+ hours a day, incredibly tired, no appetite, headaches, loose bowel movements, chest discomfort- 5/17: Appetite has slightly improved, bowel movements improved but not entirely back to normal, BP still high (132/94), pressure and fogginess in head, dry cough develops (coughing once every ten minutes or so), mid back around spine is very sore, neck feels sore as if head is too heavy, fatigue has improved and I'm able to stay awake all day, eyes feel very tired and dry, left armpit and left breast are very sore. Had a previous knee discomfort in 2020 but had gone to PT and recovered 100%, but suddenly right knee has a dull aching/pain like it did prior to physical therapy (hadn't felt discomfort in it since finishing PT 11/2020) 5/18: went to PCP to discuss symptoms, was told I was having a robust reaction to vaccine. PCP attributed coughing to allergies and told me to use Flonase and take Tylenol for headaches, PCP anticipated I would feel better in another 2-3 weeks. Was prescribed 10 mg of Propranolol 2x a day for high BP and anxious feeling 5/19: first solid bowel movement since vaccination, energy level is good, noticed an improvement in shortness of breath 5/20: chest discomfort/shortness of breath when carrying laundry to laundry room, sore neck and sore mid-back, armpit and left breast still sore 5/21: armpit, left breast, back and neck still sore, cough continues, chest discomfort continues 5/24: everything is still sore, chest pressure was better during the day but suddenly felt fluttery/palpitations at night out of nowhere 5/25: sore back, armpit and breast, coughing, endurance while doing laundry was good, in evening left breast was very sore and felt anxious/chest pressure 5/26: outside of left ankle is sore, mid/upper back sore, left boob sore, fluttery chest feeling in evening 5/29: tightness in chest, couldn't take a deep inhale, still coughing 5/30: very sore left breast, swollen left lymph node in throat, coughing, sore neck. Flonase doesn't seem to helping cough at all. 6/4: chest pressure in evening, felt like my breaths were deep even though I was just sitting on couch, still coughing, neck, back and breast continue to be sore. 6/6: first day of placebo week on hormonal birth control 6/10: took a Tylenol extra strength before bed for headache, woke up in middle of night and had significantly worse chest pain and palpitations. Also had shivers and BP was higher than it had been since going on Propranolol (137/97). 6/11: shortness of breath when talking, severe fatigue, chest pain and palpitations continued throughout day, felt very anxious. No appetite. Got tested for COVID at local pharmacy and tested negative. Cough continues. Had phone call with PCP and was advised to double Propranolol dosage to lower BP and help with anxiety. 6/12: very fatigued, slept most of day, no appetite, loose stool/diarrhea, coughing. BP was 128/90 in evening. 6/13: very fatigued, slept most of day, loose stool, no appetite, coughing. Went back to normal dosage of Propranolol because i was curious if the double dosage was worsening my fatigue and loss of appetite. BP was 126/88. 6/14: feeling slightly better, still have chest pressure, headache, fatigue, right knee is still bothering me. 6/18: fatigue/fogginess throughout day, low appetite but it's improving. right knee still bothering me. felt very panicked/fluttery in chest in evening and didn't feel I could go to the grocery store. BP was 115/80. 6/22: saw cardiologist for first time, he ordered an MRI and a health monitor patch. we spoke about potential inflammation issues and he suggested I go on a Motrin routine to see if that helps, as there are no adverse effects to taking it. This evening I took 400 mg of Motrin, and began taking 400 mg every morning and night. Scheduled follow-up cardio appt for 7/13. 6/25: good energy level, didn't need to nap. watched a scary movie and didn't feel any palpitations or pressure (previously I'd feel increased discomfort and pressure when stressed/scared since getting vaccinated). 6/26: solid stool, good energy level, cough seems lighter, good appetite 6/27: some slight chest pressure during day, solid stool, felt fluttery late at night, cough was worse than earlier in the day. in general didn't feel as good as last couple of days. BP was 115/70 in evening. 6/29: good energy and appetite, some coughing, noticed my knee isn't bothering me as much now. 6/30: very tired in morning, some fluttery chest feelings after getting up, knee discomfort is gone. 7/3: appetite and bowel movements have been good, good energy levels, some chest pressure/shortness of breath while standing in line at post office. incredibly sore boobs (about to start period, but they're even more sore than usual for this time of month). BP was 118/80 at night. 7/4: good energy level, not much coughing at all, first day of placebo week for birth control. 7/5: great energy level and appetite, had a very busy and long day and felt great throughout. 7/6: felt pretty tired today, started period. was in bed in evening and suddenly felt shortness of breath, some chest pressure. checked BP and it was high again (140/90). Had loose stool/diarrhea three times in a row at night after starting to feel chest pressure, continued to feel anxious/palpitations/pressure and felt shivery, noticed an increase in coughing. This is almost four weeks to the day of my last bad night when I had same symptoms, only this time the symptoms were less severe. On period both times, wondering if this has anything to do with it. 7/7: loose stool first thing in morning, feeling very disappointed that I had a bad chest episode the night before as it seemed that the Motrin routine had been working, but suddenly feeling bad again. Napped most of afternoon, slight chest pressure throughout day, but decent energy level and don't feel nearly as exhausted as I did on the day following my previous chest episode. Noticed my knee is bothering me again. 7/8: shortness of breath, very sore mid back, decent appetite, fatigue. Got MRI today. 7/10: some fatigue and palpitations but had an active day and was able to stay awake the whole time, had a decent appetite  Currently awaiting cardio follow-up appt

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Moderna COVID 19 vaccine EUA  Admitted inpatient for CHF exacerbation

Two concerns may indicate under/invalid dose administered.   1) Location of injection was low side of arm & may have missed muscle.   2) Immediately after injection, clear fluid leaked out of arm, beaded up and trickled down. Nurse wiped away and it repeated leaking a second time. I asked if enough dose remained to be effective she replied "I hope so ...but I don't really know" then she left. A second nurse arrived and told us we could leave without 15 minute wait if we felt fine. I asked what to do about my leaky, off target dose, and was given phone number to report to VAERS, which I called same day, but VAERS said they only report adverse symptoms not administration problems. It was suggested I notify health dept and vaccine facility, who in turn suggested a different health dept, who in turn suggested  covid vaccine info line, who in turn suggested my PCP.  My PCP advised me to go back to clinic and get re-vaccinated.  That clinic no longer exists, so my PCP then said go to any, which I attempted, but when I did I was refused because they view me as already technically dosed, if not actually dosed.  I contacted PCP a third time, and they said I should consider myself as single dosed only, I should continue masking, social distancing etc., until I get re-vaccinated or receive a booster in the autumn.  He indicated that they would not give me a written authorization because they didn?t administer the questionable shot.  He did suggest I could lie about having received a second dose and they would give me the dose.  I thought this wrong so I gave up for a while.    I am at risk for severe complications of Covid-19 due to a long history of lung problems, lung collapse, pneumonia, irregular heartbeat, age 59, etc., and I am also a caregiver for my 91 year old mother.  Due to partially vaccinated status I must still live an isolated, masked up life. It bothers me greatly when I should have received a vaccine I could be confident of.  Recently I called Pfizer to see if perhaps they could offer information and help.   They suggested I phone CDC again about invalid/under dose vaccine administration.  I did, and CDC indicated VAERS should have taken my report when I called them, and CDC encouraged me to report it by on-line form, in hope that I may yet receive a proper second dose.   While unlikely that the shot I received on April 6th was a full dose, it is conceivable I got a partial dose.  I do not wish an overdose, but I have learned that the doses in trials were much higher without problems, and it has also been almost four months since that botched dose was given to me, and I know boosters are common in many vaccines without posing undue risk of overdose.  This must be weighed against the risks of my possibly contracting Covid-19.  It is also pertinent that I live in a anti-mask, anti-vaccine part of the world, making my exposure risks even greater.  I?m no shrinking violet, but a recent visit to my doctor?s office for skin cancer follow up was unnerving, as I was squeezed into the little exam room along with nurses, a student, and the doctor, and none wore masks and only one had been vaccinated.    I write to you to inquire if you will guide a determination and authorization in my instance of re-vaccination or booster.  Please help.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: After four days of flu-like symptoms which began on evening of second Pfizer vaccine experienced hearing loss and tinnitus. DIAGNOSIS:  SUDDEN RIGHT-SIDED HEARING LOSS AND TINNITUS (ICD-H91.20 AND ICD-H93.11) TREATMENTS:  Primary Care Doctor, Dr., 3/4/21, Prescribed ZPAC and if no improvement see ENT No Improvement ENT Appointment, Dr., 3/18/21, Prescribed High Dose Prednisone beginning with 60 mg for five days and titration after from 3/18/21 to 4/8/21.  Also conducted audiological evaluation which indicated moderate to severe Sensorineural Hearing Loss (SNHL) in right ear. Ordered MRI with contrast. ENT Appointments, Dr., 3/25,/21, 4/6/21 and 5/10/21. SECOND OPINION ENT, Dr. who conducted audiologic evaulation and performed prednisone injection into right ear, 5/12/21. Followup ENT appiointment with Dr. on 6/9/21 in which he referred me to an Otolarynologists, Dr. at facility in another area. OTOLARYNOLOGIST APPOINTMENT, Met with Dr., 7/6/21 for evaluation.  He indicated that hearing loss and tinnitus are permanent and suggested I move forward with trying hearing aids, two types, which he indicated would not work.  He said the only solution that would restore my hearing and eliminate the tinnitus is a cochlear implant.  In order to be considered a candidate it is necessary to try the hearing aid route first.   ENT APPOINTMENT with Dr. and Audiologist is scheduled for 7/29/21 to explore hearing aid options and path forward.
LAB_DATA: MRI WITH CONTRAST, 3/19/21,  NEGATIVE FOR ACOUSTIC SCHWANNOMA AUDIOLOGIC EVALUATIONS, 3/18/21, 3/25/21, 4/6/21, 5/10/21, 5/12/21, 6/9/21, MODERATELY SEVERE SNHL.

During registration there was miscommunication due to language barrier and the father was registered instead of the 17 year old son.  Moderna vaccine was administered when it should have been Pfizer.   I as the clinical lead realized an administration error had been made when the wayfinder handed me a blue prevax form for Pfizer and there was no Pfizer on the floor (they were locked in the med room). We immediately brought the 17 year old patient and the father to an exam room and informed them about the error (wrong patient was registered and Moderna was given instead of Pfizer).  They were both very understanding and did not have questions or concerns.

The Dr. felt that I was having an allergic reaction to the vaccine. He ran bloodwork and monitored me for the day. I went home and continued to feel terrible with my symptoms persisting, especially the rapid heartbeat and shortness of breath. A few weeks later I was diagnosed with pneumonia which exacerbated my asthma. It was difficult to breathe and I started developing issues with throat tightness and swallowing as well. I was prescribed prednisone, antibiotics and additional inhalers to help relieve the symptoms. I had a throat and swallow test done and was diagnosed with vocal chord dysphonia. I am currently doing voice therapy to help with that. I don't know if the pneumonia and other problems are a direct result of the vaccine but I do know that I didn't have these issues prior to getting the vaccine so I felt it was important to report it. Please feel free to contact me if you have any questions.

She was subsequently found to have a pericardial effusion s/p pericardiocentesis and drain placement on 6/30. Fluid analysis was not indicative of bacterial pericarditis and blood+pericardial fluid cultures are no growth (fluid 37% neutrophils, 54% monos, 5% lymphs, normal glucose. Reportedly 750 mL of straw colored fluid was removed during the pericardiocentesis. The pericardial drain was left in place. RPR is negative. Path report from 6/30 pericardial fluid indicated no malignant cells seen, "by immunochemistry the epithelial cells are positive for cytokeratin 7, calretinin and WT-1, and negative for estrogen receptor, GATA-3, BerEP4, CDX-2, PAX-8, Claudin-4, TTF-1, p40, and keratin 20. Reactive mesothelial cells are favored." Unfortunately she did have subsequent reaccumulation of her pericardial fluid s/p redrain and growing Proteus on 7/8, now being treated as a suppurative pericarditis. Following my second Pfizer dose on on 4/2/21 I began having a strong burning pain in my right forearm and wrist area. I perceived this initially to be carpal tunnel and it started on 4/5/21. I self treated with ibuprofen for a few days with no improvement, then saw my PCP on 4/9.  My PCP thought this to be tenosynivitis, and prescribed Methylprednislone. The steroid treatment helped for the first few days but then the pain quickly spread to my right leg in the thigh area. Same type of pain, burning and intense. I was able to walk, but with a slight limp.  I saw my PCP again on 4/15 to discuss the new symptoms. He began researching possible conditions and also ordered some blood tests for common auto-immune diseases (Uric Acid, C-Reactive Protein, CMP, ANA). Everything returned normal except for C-Reactive (value- 50+). To be sure it wasn?t a case of septic arthritis, I was placed on an antibiotic on 4/17 (Keflex) for 7 days.  The Keflex did not help and actually gave me a slight fever (100.1) and I missed work on 4/19,20,21. I started to improve on 4/16 but the symptoms were still present.  As a followup, my PCP ordered a more comprehensive blood panel to be reviewed at my next appointment on 4/30. The following blood tests were ordered: TSH 3rd Gen Blood, CBC, CMP (BAMP, TP ALB TBIL,ALK, AST, ALT), and LIPID Panel.   On PCP appointment on 4/30, my symptoms continued to present in legs and right arm. All values from blood tests were normal. He ordered a lower back xray, which was scheduled for 5/11. At this point, my PCP referred me to a rheumetologist as he had exhausted his options.  Unfortunately, the earliest rheumatology available was 5/18.  On 5/18 appointment with rheumatology resulted in more tests: Parvovirus B19, Rheumatoid Factor, Serum Protein Electrophoresis, Urine PRotein/Creatinine Ratio, Immunoglobulin Assay-Blood, Immunofixation Procedure Blood, ASO- Blood, CPK Blood, Cyclic Citrullinated Peptide Antb, Hep B Surface AG, Hep C AB- Blood, Microalbumin urine random. All tests read as negative or normal except ASO.  Rheumetologist referred me to Infectious Disease for further testing on 5/26, which resulted in the following blood tests: Ehrlichia Chaffeensis AB IGG, DNASE B Antibody, HLA Typing A B C Single - Blood, Legionnella -Blood, Prostate Specific Antigen, Unrinanalysis with Microscopic, Chlamydia and GC RNA AMP, Upper respiratory throat culture. He also ordered an ECG, a chest XRAY (PA and Lateral), CT scan of the pelvis. On 6/4 at a followup appointment, he ordered Crypto AG and C-Reactive Protein. At this point, CRP value was 180.74.  I worked my last day of work on 5/14 as the pain became too intense to manage. As the week progressed, I slowly lost my ability to walk and care for myself. I could walk only 10-15 feet at a time, and doing so would cause a severe flare-up of pain in my legs. I was mostly bedridden for 2 weeks starting on 5/20 and was only getting up very minimally. I needed a wheelchair for transport to my appointments on 5/25, 5/26, 6/2, 6/3. By 6/4, I was barely able to walk to that appointment, but the office is very small so I was able to make a short distance.  My rheumetologist, having reviewed all my normal test results ordered an EMG on my legs and right arm and also an MRI on my lumbar and cervical.  EMG conducted on 6/24 and revealed some nerve damage and signs of neuropathy in my legs; and also carpal tunnel in the right wrist.  MRI Lumbar (6/25) revealed some common lower back issues, but nothing affecting the nerves that may be the cause of my symptoms. MRI Cervical (7/12) completed but yet to be analyzed.   As of today, July 12, I?m feeling much improved over how I felt in early June. I can walk a short distance of ? mile without needing a break. I have lost muscle tone and need to work on getting my strength back. My right arm has minimal pain but will flareup with heavy computer usage.  However, for the past 2 weeks, my left arm (which has been symptom free since April) now has a similar burning pain that starts at the funnybone of the elbow and runs up to my wrist. The pain comes and goes but is sometimes very intense and can be debilitating. It is hard for me to open some doors with this hand or even hold a heavy cup of water.  As a previously healthy person, and having done exhaustive testing, myself and my PCP believe I had a rare and negative reaction to the vaccine.
LAB_DATA: 4/15/21 - Uric Acid, C-Reactive Protein, CMP, ANA = all normal/negative except CRP (value 50)  4/26/21 - TSH 3rd Gen Blood, CBC, CMP (BAMP, TP ALB TBIL,ALK, AST, ALT), and LIPID Panel. = all normal  5/11/21 - Lumbar Xray = normal for age and condition, not believe to affect current symptoms  5/18/21 - Parvovirus B19, Rheumatoid Factor, Serum Protein Electrophoresis, Urine PRotein/Creatinine Ratio, Immunoglobulin Assay-Blood, Immunofixation Procedure Blood, ASO- Blood, CPK Blood, Cyclic Citrullinated Peptide Antb, Hep B Surface AG, Hep C AB- Blood, Microalbumin urine random. All tests read as negative or normal except ASO.  5/14/21 - Lyme Western BLT, C Reactive Protein. = Negative for Lyme, C-reactive value now 87.04  5/26/21 - Ehrlichia Chaffeensis AB IGG, DNASE B Antibody, HLA Typing A B C Single - Blood, Legionnella -Blood, Prostate Specific Antigen, Unrinanalysis with Microscopic, Chlamydia and GC RNA AMP, Upper respiratory throat culture.  5/26/21 - ECG 12-LEAD - "Otherwise normal - tachycardia rate 99"  5/28/21 - Xray Chest PA and Lateral = normal  6/3/21 - CT Abdomen/Pelvis - normal  6/4/21 - Glycohemoglobin Total Blood - normal; Crypto AG - negative, C Reactive Protein value 180.74  6/24/21 - EMG - Sensorimotor Peripheral Neuropathy of bilateral extremities; Moderate Right Carpal Tunnel Syndrome  6/25/21 - MRI Lumbar - no nerve damage, but other issues present  7/12/21 -MRI Cervical - no analysis yet

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Immediately upon receiving injection I had tingling/numbness in my left arm that went all the way to my hand. I had weakness in my left hand.  25 minutes after injection my numbness significantly intensified and I had contracture of the left hand. I also experienced tingling of the lips, tongue and face.  Within a couple minutes my right hand also began to experience contractures. At this same time my heart started racing and i had difficulty breathing (likely hyperventilation due to stress).  Once I arrived at the emergency room a ecg was completed. The contractures went away, but re-emerged multiple times. My ionized calcium was found to be low (1.11 mmol/L), but no other notable lab abnormalities.  This persisted for a few hours and finally went away.
LAB_DATA: ionized calcium 1.11 mmol/L

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Chief Complaint   hypoxia  History of Present Illness     Pt is a 67F with PMH of COPD, depression, anxiety, possible Afib, possible CHF who presented as a transfer from OSH for hypoxia in the setting of COPD exacerbation and COVID PNA. She also has a hx of left lower lobe lobectomy many years ago for an infection per patient report. She states that she typically wears 4L o2 at home while sleeping and with exertion, but does not require any at rest. She reports that she completed both COVID vaccines about 1-2 months ago. She did have contact with her daughter who also tested positive recently. She reports that she started to feel dyspneic with minimal exertion at home and took her O2 saturations and found them to be in the 70s, so she presented to the ED. She underwent CTA scan in ED and was found to have left lower lobe collapse, severely calcified and ulcerated thoracic aorta with possible intraluminal hanging thrombus and small penetrating aortic ulcer. She was sent here for further work up and management. She denies any etoh or drug use, but has smoked 1-2ppd for 50 years. Mom and dad with hx of cancer. She denies any fevers, chills, chest pain, tightness, pressure, or worsening dyspnea at rest. She does have a productive cough with yellow sputum production and dyspnea with exertion.
HISTORY: PMH of COPD, depression, anxiety, possible Afib, possible CHF

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Received Moderna vaccines on 2/11/21 and 3/11/21. Tested positive for COVID-19 by PCR on 7/9/2021. Will received monoclonal antibody therapy.

I had my vaccine on May 18, 2021.  Prior to this date I was in good health.  I was in remission from  Ankylosing Spondylitis and Rheumatoid Arthritis for a 3 year period of time. I was off all meds related to this.  I was active and I am not over weight.  ( I have HBP and thyroid issues....All controlled).   After the vaccine, beginning around May 27, 2021 I started experiencing bi-lateral shoulder pain and my knees began to get stiff.  within the next week and after the symptoms got worse and started affecting all major joints.  I had a routine appointment with my Rheumatologist on June 21, but I called to been seen sooner because it was becoming difficult to stand, walk and the pain in my shoulders was severe and referred pain down my arms to my elbows.  I had an appointment on June 14, 2021 and had a blood test on the 18th.  The report came back with the highest numbers that I have ever had for inflammation.  There has been a lot of confusion at my doctors office but they are finally getting me approved to go back on biologics. I have been unable to do any of my normal activities and the pain throughout my body is a solid 10 on a 1-10 scale.  There isnt any relief currently and I am struggling.
LAB_DATA: June 18, 2021 Blood test ordered by Rheumatologist, ESR and Reactive Protien are well above the normal range.
OTHER_MEDS: Levothyroxine; Atenolol; Sertraline; multi-vitamin; Osteo Bi-flex; Vitamin D
HISTORY: Was in remission for Rheumatoid Arthritis for 3 years

Transferred to Hospital, underwent emergent LHC, did not show infarction and had normal epicardial anatomy. TTE was normal. CTA confirmed LLL small Pulmonary Embolism. Was started on Xarelto. She had an NSTEMI type II subendocardial injury secondary to V. fib arrest in context of PE or arrhythmia. Cardiac MRI with scar likely secondary to myocarditis. Started by cardiology on colchicine. Unknown etiology for pulmonary embolism, perhaps result of arrest/cpr.  Had ICD placed.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient admitted fur to chest pain and dyspnea and found to have myopericarditis after 2nd dose of COVID-19 Pzifer vaccine. Vaccine was administered at pharmacy.  First dose received on 5/15/2021, second dose on 6/5/2021. Fatigue and chills started a few hours after second dose and then developed shortness of breath, nausea, emesis and 8/10 midsternal chest pain. Presented to an urgent care facility where CXR and EKG were obtained. EKG showed early repolarizations. Labs were obtained at a local ED and showed elevated troponins, initially 11k and then to 20k and peaked there. BNP was within normal limits. Subsequent EKG showed diffuse ST-segment elevations concerning for acute pericarditis. No prior infections or symptoms like this previously. He was given colchicine at outside facility prior to transfer. At hospital he was continued on ibuprofen and monitored with telemetry and had ECHO and cardiac MRI. Latter was consistent with myopericarditis. ECHO showed normal function. He received PPI while on NSAIDs. His symptoms resolved and he was discharged to home on 6/10/2021 with activity restrictions and plan to follow-up with peds cardiology. Of note, there was an error submitting the initial VAERS report for this patient during the admission, therefore, this delayed report is being submitted.

Epicardial enhancement on LGE imaging in mid and apical left ventricular free wall and apical interventricular septum consistent with myopericarditis (non-ischemic distribution) ECHO 6/8/2021: Normal LV. NO pericardial effusion.

On the same day I got the vaccine and the next day, I had fever, body aches, and malaise; I was in bed for 2 days. I had a lack of energy that was worse than it had been before the vaccine. On or about 4/14/2021, I woke up at about 2:00AM with chest pain, pain in the left shoulder and in the left side of the neck. The symptoms subsided after some time. I had low oxygen saturation levels; I knew this, because I used a pulse oximeter that had been used by my late husband. The low oxygen saturation levels have been ongoing ever since, and I have had periods of rapid heart rate and oxygen levels that are even lower than the low levels I have experienced since the vaccine. I have also had periods of chest pains at times, so my PCP referred me to both a pulmonologist and a cardiologist.
LAB_DATA: The pulmonologist ran several tests (chest CT scan, chest X-ray, pulmonary function, echocardiogram). He concluded I have post-COVID syndrome. He says that there is already lung damage; he believes that the damage began when I had COVID in March-April 2020 and that it has been exacerbated by the vaccine. He won't know if it's an autoimmune reaction until he follows my situation further; if the damage progresses, that indicates that it is an autoimmune reaction. The cardiologist examined the results of the tests performed by the pulmonologist, and he believes I have pericarditis, which is common among people who have had COVID and gotten the vaccine. More tests are pending.
OTHER_MEDS: T3 and T4 compound medication for hypothyroidism, magnesium supplement, prescription progesterone, vitamin D3, vitamin C.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 20 year old, male patient came in for his appointment for Janssen COVID vaccine. Patient filled out the vaccine questionnaire, and we discussed patient questions and common side effects. Patient did not state any adverse reaction to previous vaccine or fainting history on the vaccine questionnaire. Patient was given vaccine in left arm. Shortly after receiving vaccine, patient states, "uh-oh it's happening again." I asked patient what was happening and he stated, "this happened to me when I got a blood draw. I fainted."  I told patient to take some deep breaths, patient started to stare off to the ceiling and his pupils were dilated and his head fell back in the chair towards the ceiling. His legs body became stiff and he lost consciousness in the chair.  I called for help and she came to assist me in the immunization room. I ran to get him a water while the pharmacy called for 911. He regained consciousness quickly, within a minute.  Emergency response came quickly and attended to him and took his blood pressure and vitals. He was able to drink water and respond to all questions. He refused to be taken to the hospital and did not think he needed any additional medical attention. He was advised to follow up with his primary care physician. He was advised to sit and stay and get a ride home, which he did.  An incident report and VAERS report will be reported today.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: At approximately 1058, patient reported feeling lightheaded in vaccination chair. Painted closed eyes and slumped over in vaccination chair. Patient was slumped over for approximately 2 seconds.  Nurse supported patient in vaccination chair. Patient opened her eyes immediately. Patient was alert and oriented to person, place, time and situation. Patient reported urinating in chair. Patient reported severe needle phobia, anxiety disorder and history of urination when exposed to needles. Patient given water. Patient able to drink water. Patient offered anti-gravity chair. Two nurses assisted patient into anti-gravity chair. At 1101, nurse assessed patient vital signs: blood pressure 107/84 mmHg, pulse 70 beats/minute, and SpO2 98%. At 1110, patient vital signs reassessed: blood pressure 110/80 mmHg, pulse 80 beats/minute, and SpO2 98%. Patient reported feeling dizzy. Patient given juice. Patient able to juice. At 1120, nurse reassessed patient vital signs: blood pressure 110/82 mmHg, pulse 76 beats/minute, and SpO2 98%. Patient report she felt "better". At 1132, patient reassessed. Patient reported not feeling anxious. Patient able to stand and reported feeling "a little lightheaded". Patient offered to stay for further observation. Patient refused to stay for further observation. Lead nurse educated patient on signs/symptoms of when to seek emergency care, to sign up on v-safe, and to follow up with primary care provider. At 1133, patient left facility with steady gait and unlabored respirations.
HISTORY: Anxiety disorder; severe needle phobia; depression

SYMPTOM_TEXT: On May 19th, nineteen days after my second Pfizer vaccine, I collapsed at the farmer's market. I was vomiting, sweating intensely, with my heart racing at 180 bpm.  A stranger called 911 and I was given adenosine in the ambulance to stop my heart to break the cycle and reset my heart rhythm. I could have died. After multiple tests in the hospital,  I was told that I had SVT supra ventricular tachycardia.  A second cardiac episode occurred on June 1st, and I was once again given adenosine in the ambulance to stop my racing heart at 190 BPM and taken to the hospital where I stayed for 2 days.  After speaking with several cardiologists, I was told that I had to have a heart procedure.  On June 21,  I had a heart ablation, and I am still recovering.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I was tired. I wake up in the middle of night. I could not move. In May, I got the bad headache in the back of head and neck. It was so bad I had to go to the doctor. She did a neuro exam and give me a presentation for my headache. She gave me Flexural for my neck pain. I feel like after I got the vaccine it throw me into full menopause.

On May 13th, I felt my feet go numb and I could not stand. I sat down to immediately find a heat go through my bod - heat to head. I then felt my heart racing. Took my pulse and it was 134. (I have had no heart issues at all previously - normal resting heart rate in the 60s). Three more times this happened, with heat going from feet to head (numbness in feet).  Each heart rate was progressively lower with each incidence.  Then it stopped. This was in the afternoon and by evening felt ok.   The 14th, the same thing happened but only 3 times and with hr incidents starting at 123.  Then fine again.  The morning of the 15th started again, so I went to urgent care appointment in the afternoon. By this time, my heart rate was up and down..  They ran an EKG and it was fine, just showing rapid heart rate. But I was sent to the ER for further tests.  At  ER another EKG, chest x-ray and blood work.  Only item of significance was an elevated TSH.  At this point, my heart rate was going up and down (I had a finger monitor so I could watch it).  I'll note at this point, the heart rate was random but I was able to walk. Over the next week or so, hr got worse and positional. When I stood up, it would sky rocket to the 140s.  I became shaky, developed brain fog, nausea, feeling like I was going to fall over and felt only well laying down or sitting.  I visited my primary who initially thought anxiety but as symptoms were getting worse (I could no longer do anything: walk farther than from the living room to the kitchen, do simple tasks while standing or sitting - hr would increase while doing activities even while sitting, and no longer drive).My doctor decided it was more than anxiety when I was continuing to have symptoms that looked like POTS. I have been to the cardiologist - she  did a 24 holter and EKG - no significance, but decided my heart was not the primary cause of the positional heart rate increase.  I am due for an echocardiogram this week - just to make sure but she did not think that was the issue. An MRI this week, recommended by my neurologist. and have done preliminary blood work/urinalysis for possible endocrine issues - all that have come back normal so far (but seeing an endocrinologist next month anyway).  I currently am seeing functional neurologist who has diagnosed me with dysautonomia  (so far of unknown reasons) - he is helping me with the heart rate issue (POTS) and other symptoms that have developed over the weeks like electrical zaps throughout my body - some sort of neruopathy. I was in great health until this shot.  I had not even had a cold since January of 2020.  I may have hypothyroidism but it has been managed with some ups and downs in TSH for the last 20 years with no other issues.   Some of my doctors do not correlate the shot to my problem but some have.  There does not seem to be any other explanation.
LAB_DATA: See above
OTHER_MEDS: Synthroid magnesium supplement turmeric supplement bee pollen supplement cbd oil

SYMPTOM_TEXT: PT is a 17 y/o previously healthy boy who presents with 3 days of moderate-severe, substernal chest pain, dyspnea, and nausea 2 days after receiving the 2nd dose of the Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine. On Tuesday (7/6), PT received the second Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine. The following day (Wednesday 7/7) PT had "flu-like symptoms" with chills, subjective fever, and a sore arm that resolved by Thursday (7/8). He was back to his baseline state of health on Thursday (7/8) and felt fine that whole day. On Friday afternoon (7/9) when he was at work washing dishes where he had some physical exertion he began to notice at 16:30-17:00 that he developed substernal, sharp, 7/10 chest pain that did not radiate, improve/worsen with deep breaths, sitting up, laying down or with movement of his upper extremities. It worsened towards the end of the night and peaked at 8/10 by 22:00-23:00 that same evening. His sister picked him up from work per his regular routine and he went home and took a shower which improved the pain to a 5-6/10 when he went to sleep. He woke up at 3 AM on Saturday (7/10) AM and had one episode of NBNB emesis associated with the chest pain. When he woke up later that morning he felt improved until 10-12 AM he developed mild chest pain again which he took Tums for. He also tried Motrin which did not help his pain at all. On the morning of admission (7/11), he woke up at 6-7 AM with upper right back pain, dyspnea, and nausea along with the persistent chest pain which prompted him to present to MFSH. He does endorse mild sore throat but denies any fevers, recent sick contacts, known COVID-19 exposure or previous history of COVID-19. There is a family history of cardiac disease including a fatal MI in his father. His mother's family also has a history of heart disease and both sides have a history of high cholesterol. He did add Whey Protein recently to his diet to for muscle building, but he DENIES any drug, alcohol, tobacco, vaping, marijuana, THC use. He does not play any sports regularly. He also denies any recent bug/tick bites or rashes.
LAB_DATA: PT is a 17 y/o previously healthy boy who presented with 3 days of moderate-severe, substernal chest pain, dyspnea, and nausea 2 days after receiving the 2nd dose of the Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine found to have elevated troponins at 3.36 and ST elevation, probably early repolarization on EKG consistent with perimyocarditis. 7/11 Cardiac ECHO showed "Normal biventricular systolic function. No pericardial effusion." He was initially admitted to the PICU. His initial CBC showed a mild leukocytosis with normal BMP, Ca, Mg, and Phos. Troponins were trended q8h and were downtrending (1.59 <- 2.91 <- 3.36) at the time of discharge.   - He remained asymptomatic and hemodynamically stable throughout his entire admission and his physical exam at the time of discharge was significant for "Regular rate and rhythm; normal S1/S2. No murmurs, rubs, or gallops. Capillary refill <2 seconds. 2+ Radial pulses. No tibial edema present."

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Two twins were in for their 4 month old check up as a new patient in our office on 6/23/21. They were due for vaccinations: Rotavirus, DTap-HIB-IPV, and PCV-13. We administered Rotavirus and PCV-13 with correct vaccinations, however we inadvertently administered Kinrix (DTap-IPV) instead of Pediarix (DTap-HepB-IPV) or Pentacel (DTap-HIB-IPV). Kinrix is approved for children 4-6 years of age whereas Pediarix is approved for children 6 weeks of age - 6 years of age, and Pentacel is approved for 6 weeks - 4 years of age.  Kinrix: GlaxoSmithKline vaccine, 0.5 mL intramuscular injection of DTap/IPV  This mistake of administering Kinrix was made due to lack of information on vaccine packaging (it did not provide age ranges on the box or in the package insert) and my human error. After reviewing CDC and vaccination guidelines/information on this event, it was found that this would not be harmful to the babies, the brand was just not tested/approved for children at 4 months old. It was the same dosage as the other, approved vaccines for their age with the same content being administered for DTap and IPV to immunize the twins.  The information for the vaccines administered were entered in the patient's chart, Kinrix was documented as out of age range, transmitted to the registry, and I have reached out to registry to ensure that this would be approved on his immunization record toward his immunization status (it is dependent on the individual's state guidelines). The parents were notified of this event on 6/23, and I explained to them everything that happened and ensured them of the safety of their children. I apologized for this human error and made sure they were on the same page with all their questions and concerns.  They were monitored closely and did not have any adverse reactions to this vaccine and it was confirmed by our state guidelines and immunization nurse through registry that this will count toward the twins' immunization status.  We took measures to prevent this from happening in the future by labelling the boxes to make it very clear that Kinrix is for 4-6 year olds and Pediarix is 6 weeks-6 years and Pentacel is 6 weeks-4 years. We also created a schedule for immunization based on the vaccines we have in our office clearly marking for each age range and vaccine type required. All staff members were informed of this situation to learn from this mistake.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: About 4 days after second shot, I noticed I had bumps on by back side.   They did not itch.   I though they were from bike riding - chafing.    But they moved around.   10 days after, my lip started to swell pretty badly while I was in a meeting.   Got online with doctor was told to go to hospital.  Anaphylaxis was the diagnosis.    They gave standard care - steroids, antihistamine, pepcid, etc.    Issue went away including the bumps on behind.    Was told to go my doctor. Went to my doctor.   Said dont worry, likely will not come back again.   Just a reaction of some type.      Next night lip swelled up - other side of mouth.  Online doctor said to go emergency room.    Back to emergency same treatment - more steroids, pecid, antihistamine.   Back  to my doctor and he sends me to alergist.   I have never had an allergic reaction to anything in my life.   Allergist said the reaction is due to the covid shot and making my immune system go crazy.   He put me on regimen of pepcid and antihistamine.    Seems to work for about a week - but then the hives came back.   More swelling of the face (lips, eyes) but none bad enough to go to hospital.    Taking meds 3 to 4 times a day (pepcid and antihistamine).     Had swelling in the ankle which the doctor said basically hives gone crazy.   Then the hives got worse - and itching.   Covered most of my body.    The hives on the bottom of the feet felt like walking on air pillow packaging material.    Dr puts me back on steroids.    Go through this process twice with steroids.    Dr said we would have to go the route of Xolair.   Received first injection three weeks ago.    But after shot had bad hives again with itching this time  - more steroids.     Then things sort of leveled out - still had hives but not a large - and no itching _ thank goodness.     But then on 7-2-21 I woke up with severe swelling of the face - and into the throat.    Had difficulty swallowing.    Back to emergency room again - more shots and Epinephrine.     They prescribe more steroids and epi pen just in case because the reaction was so severe.    Second shot of Xolair is in one more week - hopefully gets things under control.
OTHER_MEDS: Verapamil, iron 60 mg, multivitamin, Saw palmetto

SYMPTOM_TEXT: On Apr 10, 2021, it was the 2nd dose of the COVID-19 Moderna vaccines. (The 1st dose was on Mar 12, 2021).  Both times were done at the.  No significant symptoms happened after the 1st dose.  However, there were reactions after the 2nd dose.  Right after the 2nd dose, that night and the 2 days after, I had high fevers in the range of 100.4 to 101.5.  I also had significant episodes of chills, i.e. feeling uncontrollably cold and shivering, even though I was having high fevers.  Afterwards the fevers and the chills subsided.  I thought all was OK again, and no big deal.  However, on May 01, 2021; I experienced significant chest pain on the left side of the chest (near the heart area).  I could not figure out what caused the pain as I did not have any heavy physical activities.  I thought I had indigestion, but the heart-burn medicine did not help.  As the chest pain intensified, and my blood pressure climbing up to around 125 / 70 to 127 / 70 (my typical normal blood pressure was about 95 / 65),  I was afraid of having a heart attack, so at around 7 PM, I went to the Urgent Care facility, Patient First, in.  They told me that I should go to a Hospital ER.  So, around 8 PM, I went. There they did a lot of tests, and told me I did not have a heart attack nor blood clots, but I had some bad inflammation of unknown pathology.  They also said my EKG had changes and they were concerned because of that change, but they could not figure out the reason.  The ER doctor ordered and I was given an injection of a strong anti-inflammatory medicine.   After keeping me there until almost 2 AM to 3 AM of the following early morning, they discharged me when the symptoms reduced.  I remembered, about 30 minutes after receiving the injection of the anti-inflammatory medicine, the chest pain got lessened, and my heart pressure went back down to about 115 / 70 (It was 127/70 when I checked into the ER).  All in all, it was a really scary event for me that night.  At first, I did not associate this event with the COVID-19 vaccine.  However, after reading many news articles about the possibility of COVID-19 vaccine-induced heart inflammation, I believed I should report this adverse reaction (chest pain) event, and all other adverse reactions I experienced, to the system. I'd like the scientists beware that the reactions of chest pain could also happen to older (female) adults.
LAB_DATA: I don't know all the details about lab tests given to me on May 01 and May 02 2021, but I was told my heart's ECG had some change, and also I was told I had an overall inflammatory reaction to something.
OTHER_MEDS: None take 48 hours before and 48 hours after the vaccination
CUR_ILL: No acute illnesses at the time of vaccination

There, they looked in my nose and she said it was stuffy and goopy. She wasn't convinced it was an infection so told me to wait until. On Monday, Tuesday and Wednesday, I worked all day and was exhausted when I went home and on Wed, 16th, I started taking the antibiotic, I just felt bad and felt really stuffy. Got a low-grade fever, was taking Tylenol. I felt went really bad and I went as a walk-in to my primary care doctor. She said to let whatever it was to take its course. I had a little bout of nausea that would come here and there (she said that was from the drip in the back of my throat). Thursday night, I got dehydrated because I wasn't drinking enough or eating enough, nothing sounded good, though. I had a really bad headache and I passed out, woke up very quickly though. I woke up and felt nauseated. Husband took me to ER. They did an EKG and other testing including COVID test, positive result. Zinc; vitamin D, I started taking it every day instead of three days a week and added vitamin C and the elderberry gummies with immune support. I drank 7-8 bottles of water with electrolytes in it a day. I was in bed for three days without getting up. I got a pulse oximeter (as instructed by nurse at ER), never got below 90. The virus never went into my chest of my lungs and I never had to use my inhaler one time. I have about 90% of taste back now; I have some of my smell back. I didn't go back to work until 29th of June and I was just working short days as I was still very, very tired. About 3PM the tiredness would hit. Into this week, I'm not as tired anymore. SYMPTOM_TEXT: No Immediate effect. Not sure if events are related ! On March 24th 2021, patient received the one Janssen # 1805022 Covid vaccine, at home, from a at Home doctor.  1) On May 12th 2021, patient, at home on the vent, began getting tired, she threw up, could barely walk and eventually became totally lethargic. Her oxygen was low and the on hand nurse used the Ambu bag to get her oxygen up to 100, while I called the ENT?s. The ENT?s checked her vitals, and did an EKG. We spoke to the doctor, and although by that time she was acting somewhat ?normal?, the decision was made to take her to hospital. Her oxygen was stabilized and her CO2 at the hospital was 80. She remained in the hospital for four days.  2) On Sunday, July 4th, patient was at home on the ventilator.   Approximately 1:30 pm she seemed to become somewhat tired and she dropped her coffee cup.A little later, while eating, she threw up, spilling food and drink on her top. She seemed more tired and needed help changing her top. She sat in her recliner for a while and then she had to go to the bathroom. I took her there in a wheelchair. By the time she was ready to leave the bathroom, she was comatose and I had to lift her, she was dead weight, and place her in the wheelchair.  I rolled her to the recliner and lifted her into it.  She was then completely unconscious, with a continuously running nose and bubbles and fluid coming from her mouth ! Note: This was exactly same experience we had with her on May  12th 2021, when she was taken to hospital.   I increased her breath rate on the Vent from 16 to 20, hoping that would expel CO2. I also increased the oxygen setting on the floor concentrator to 9, her pulse oxy was stable at 90. With the help of my daughter in law and grandson, we repositioned her on the recliner to a more comfortable and accessible position, connected the AMBU bag to the oxygen and slowly applied oxygen through her trach connection.  We had also called the emergency, requesting assistance. By slowly squeezing the AMBU bag, I got her oxygen up to 100 ! Note: This Is exactly what we did on May 12 th.  The ENT?s arrived shortly and within a few minutes after they arrived, patient started to come out of her comatose condition. The ENT?s checked her vitals,(somewhat normal) did an EKG, and checked her CO2 (45).We spoke to the doctor, and by that time she was acting ?normal? ! The decision was made to keep her at home instead of going to the hospital and an at-home X-ray was ordered in case she aspirated and conducted the following day. This x-ray Did Not show any aspiration !

SYMPTOM_TEXT: About 30 min after being vaccinated with second dose Pfizer, patient reported feeling dizzy with tingling sensation in fingers. Ice pack applied to back of neck, BP taken x2 (high with no known history of HTN)- patient refused a third reading,  and juice/water was refused by patient as well. He stated his current symptoms were similar to what happens prior to anaphylaxis with shellfish. Transported to

The next evening after receiving the injection, I began to feel swelling and tenderness under my left armpit and down to the side of my left breast (same side of body as the injection site). The pain and swelling increased over the weekend, and I could not relax my left arm down to my side in its natural position without discomfort. There was no noticeable discoloration of skin, but visible swelling. I called in to my PCP's on-call doctor who explained that this could be a swelling of the lymph nodes, a side effect of the vaccine. He suggested applying alternating ice and heating pad to relieve discomfort and said the pain and swelling should recede within the next 14 days. He advised if the symptoms continued after 14 days, to make an appointment for a mammogram/ultra sound to investigate further. As he predicted, the pain and swelling receded over the next several days, and I thought all was well.  However, nearly exactly 30 days later on May 30, I began to notice tenderness and swelling in the exact same area. Though the discomfort and swelling was not as pronounced, it was noticeable. And depending on my activity (lifting, cleaning), it became more or less pronounced. At one point, the swelling seemed to be altering the appearance of my left breast, as if it was being weighted down (left breast hanging lower than the right).  I received a referral for a mammogram and ultrasound, which were taken on June 16 (see below results). Since May 30 when swelling/discomfort resumed for the second time post-vaccination, it has receded some, but continues to be more or less noticeable depending on my activity (lifting, cleaning, etc.).
LAB_DATA: Mammogram and ultrasound of left breast and lymph node area were taken on June 16. I was called by office staff that same day and was informed that there did not seem to be any lumps in the left breast, but that my lymph nodes were "increased in size".  Results on mailed paperwork also indicated, "Your exam shows findings with a high probability of being benign (non-cancerous). Short-term follow-up is recommended. Return in 3 months for a follow-up breast evaluation: ultrasound of left breast" However, I then received a second follow-up letter informing me that doctor would like to do the follow-up ultrasound in 1 month instead of 3. I am currently awaiting an appointment to be scheduled for the follow-up ultrasound of the left breast and lymph node areas.
OTHER_MEDS: Albuterol inhaler for asthma, as needed.
HISTORY: Asthma, chondromalacia patella in both knees, allergies, eczema, and heat rash.
ALLERGIES: Hydrocortisone cream and Vitamin E oil. Tree nuts (except almonds and macadamia nuts). Pome fruits (apples, peaches, nectarines, etc). Honeydew and cantaloupe melon. Dust, mold, and animal dander. Some soaps, lotions, perfumes, scented candles. Some plants and flowers. Chinese Elm tree. Skin irritation from adhesive bandages and heat rash.

Patient received Moderna COVID-19 Vaccines at outside facility on 4/1/21 and 5/19/21. On 7/11/21, patient presented to ED with sudden onset right eye vision loss while driving earlier that night.  He states that he completely lost vision in the right eye for 2 to 3 minutes.  It has since come back but now is blurred.  He denies any headache or eye pain. Visual acuity screening reveals Right Eye 20/25, L Eye 20/20 and bilateral 20/25. The pupil is reactive.  There is no evidence of retinal detachment by ultrasound. CT CTA did not reveal any evidence of carotid artery disease. COVID-19 status positive on 7/12/21. Patient is admitted to the inpatient unit with neurology consult. Neurology assessment: description sounds highly consistent with amaurosis fugax, and in the setting of known extensive cardiac history and possible hypercoagulability in the setting of positive COVID, would be concerned for an embolic event. Positive COVID despite getting Moderna vaccine x2. No respiratory symptoms, but concern for possible hypercoagulability event (embolic TIA causing some transient right eye vision loss). Patient is still admitted as of 7/12/21 with additional tests being performed.
LAB_DATA: PCR COVID-19 Positive on 7/12/21
HISTORY: History of CABG x 1, Closure of ruptured sinus of Valsalva aneurysm, Resection of right atrial mass, Repair of aortic valve, and Pericardial closure with CorMatrix due to congenital aneurysm of sinus of Valsalva and anomalous course of right coronary artery.

I was sent for xrays of my neck & shoulder, which shows some degenerative disks.  I was then sent to see a spin Dr. and did 13 weeks of physical therapy so I could have an MRI done.  The MRI didn't look like it was causing the problem so I was then sent for a nerve test, which also showed OK. I also have dizzyness & lightheadness.    I had  issues before  4/28 apt. but not so servere so not sure exactly when they started.  I had gone into VAERS to see if I could find any other people with similiar problems and did so I am now filling out this form.

This spontaneous case was reported by a patient family member or friend and describes the occurrence of LOSS OF CONSCIOUSNESS (briefly Blacked out), FALL (Fell) and HUMERUS FRACTURE (Broke his right proximal humerus) in 79-year-old male patient who received apixaban (Eliquis) for an unknown indication. On 14-Apr-2021, the patient experienced LOSS OF CONSCIOUSNESS (seriousness criterion medically significant), FALL (seriousness criterion medically significant), HUMERUS FRACTURE (seriousness criterion medically significant), CONTUSION (Bruised his right knee) and LIP INJURY (Split open his upper lip). At the time of the report, LOSS OF CONSCIOUSNESS, FALL, HUMERUS FRACTURE, CONTUSION and LIP INJURY outcome was unknown. Patient was taking Eliquis at the time he fell and broke his arm. He had been gardening and was wearing old, worn sneakers when they went to a hardware store for some supplies. At one point he slipped and fell forward to the floor. SYMPTOM_TEXT: SORE ALL OVER THE BODY; WEAKNESS IN BODY; HEADACHES; POSSIBLE BLOOD CLOT IN RIGHT LEG; SWELLING IN BOTH FEET; This spontaneous report received from a patient concerned a 57 year old. The patient's height, and weight were not reported. The patient's past medical history included accident affected right leg in 2010 and concurrent conditions included penicillin allergy (happened when patient was when very young) and severe back pain (from accident).  The patient received covid-19 vaccine ad26.cov2.s (suspension for injection, route of admin not reported, batch number: 043AZ1A, expiry: UNKNOWN) dose was not reported, 1 total, administered on 16-JUN-2021 on right arm for prophylactic vaccination. No concomitant medications were reported.  In JUN-2021 (week and a half after getting the vaccine), the patient had swelling in both feet but mostly in the right foot. The right foot swelled up during the day and then shrunk back down in the night. The skin looked pink and red and felt hot (warmth). The patient started noticing it when he started to experience pain in shins and then it got sore and then started to swell. The patient started noticing puffiness, soreness and warmth after. By 2 weeks it was very puffy and sore. The patient was able to walk and it was the right foot that was mainly bothering. The patient had not seen any health care professional during this time. The patient was concerned that he might had blood clot in right leg due to the fact that it was swollen, red and warm, as per the symptoms they read about. The patient had some headaches in the beginning, took aspirin, and it had improved. The patient also felt weak (weakness in body) and sore all over the body. These all had resolved except the right leg issue.  The action taken with covid-19 vaccine ad26.cov2.s was not applicable. The patient recovered from sore all over the body, weakness in body, and headaches, and had not recovered from swelling in both feet, and possible blood clot in right leg. This report was serious (Other Medically Important Condition).; Sender's Comments: V0: 20210713160-covid-19 vaccine ad26.cov2.- Possible blood clot in right leg. This event(s) is considered unassessable. The event(s) has a compatible/suggestive temporal relationship, is unlabeled, and has unknown scientific plausibility. There is no information on any other factors potentially associated with the event(s).
HISTORY: Medical History/Concurrent Conditions: Accident (resulted in severe back pain)

SYMPTOM_TEXT: One week after receiving the vaccine, my left arm became numb tingling and pins and needle feeling. It began at my shoulder and traveled down to my elbow down to my wrist to the tips of my fingers I had started my shift and the pain and numbness was so bad in my hands that I had to stop working and go to the ER. Once at the ER I was admitted for observation. I was released the next day upon my release, the pain numbness pins and needles tingling feeling travel to my right arm from the tips of my fingers to my elbow to my shoulder it then began in both feet from the tips of my toes traveled up to my knees eventually up to my thighs. It just progressed and progressed day by day eventually it hit my face my gums my tongue my lips and at that point I was afraid that it was going to go to my brain and I went back to the ER. I was released and told to go home and basically write it out. A few weeks later I had an appointment with a neurologist and it was determined that it was most likely a side effect of the vaccine. Prior to my neurologist visit I had had a phone appointment with my nurse practitioner. I had explained to her my symptoms of the burning numbness pain tingling pins and needle stabbing random feelings I was feeling in my entire body. She prescribed me the medication gabapentin. The gabapentin did help me and I also began to take vitamin B12 which I believe also help me eventually it all dissipated except for my hands and my feet it was minimal but still noticeable and aggravating. About a week and a half ago I started to get real bad numbness pain tingling burning stabbing pains in my feet and now my hands and now it is again began to travel from the tips of my toes to my ankles up to my kneecaps but I'm both sides. It's also worse now in my hands with burning and tingling and numbness which is traveled from the tips of my fingers to my wrists up to my elbows. I fear that it's recycling itself and it's going to happen all over again affecting my entire body. I did see my GP last week and I was prescribed more gabapentin I don't like taking the gabapentin and it's not really helping me this time around. I also experienced brain fog memory loss cognitive problems also. I'm thinking one thing but the words won't come out of my mouth. I forget things also. I have terrible memory issues. When I'm working and I'm talking to a member I forget what they called for and I can't remember. I sometimes can't talk or say the words right. I don't know what I'm going to do because I need to work but the numbness is so bad in my hands it makes it very difficult it also makes it difficult for me to talk because I can't say the right words and I can't remember things I forget very easily.
LAB_DATA: I have had some medical tests done I've had a CAT scan and an MRI of the brain but nothing was determined.
HISTORY: I have chronic pain numbness tingling pins and needle feelings in my feet upper legs to the knee both hands arms up to the elbows as of now. In the beginning one week after I had my shot I developed severe pain numbness burning tingling pins and needle feeling in my left arm I went to the ER. And they attributed to the vaccine. I was kept overnight for observation. I was released the next day. The numbness tingling burning pins and needles stabbing pain feelings continued to move throughout my body it traveled to both arms from my fingertips to my shoulders it traveled to both legs from the tips of my toes to my kneecaps up to my thighs it traveled to my face to my lips to my gums. It travel to my brain. I went back to the ER once I felt the numbness in my face and my tongue I was basically told to go home and write it out I was prescribed gabapentin by my GP to control the pain and the numbness and the burning and the tingling. I cannot tolerate that medication it's awful I did take and it did help me to an extent and I did get better for a while I also took vitamin B12 to help and it did help me for a while but this past few weeks the burning tingling numbness and pain pins and needles and sometimes stabbing pains every turn to my feet my legs up to my knees both hands up my arms to my elbows. And I fear it's going to start all over again and recycle itself and start to attack my body again. I did see my doctor last week and she did give me another prescription for gabapentin to control the symptoms but like I said I don't easily tolerate that medication and I don't like it. I also have brain fog and memory issues. I twist my words around and often forget what I'm talking about mid sentence. I sometimes can't find the words for my thoughts that I want to express. I easily forget things. And I become confused easily. It makes me nervous to drive because my feet are numb and my legs are numb and I don't know what's going to happen my vision also gets blurry and I developed a floater in my right eye. All this is very debilitating for me and it's hard for me to function like this and I don't know what I'm going to do or how I'm going to work. I did see a neurologist and he just basically told me to keep taking the gabapentin I will make it another appointment with him though and get the diagnosis.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Dose 1 was given on 1/9/21.  Dose 2 was given on 2/6/21 Lot #042L20A. 12 hours after receiving the 2nd dose I had chills, and had a fever that reached 103 degrees.  I was very tired & had body aches.  The symptoms stopped approximately  24 hours later.   The morning of 6/29/21 at approximately 5:30 am, as I was getting ready for work, my upper body became numb & collapsed.  I began coughing & coughed up frank blood.  I was lethargic & having difficulty keeping my eyes open, and chest pain on my right side.  I was transported to  Hospital via ambulance.    My troponin levels were elevated & after a Chest CT, they found a lung nodule on my upper right lung.  I was diagnosed with myocarditis & the lung nodule.  I was hospitalized & had an echocardiogram the next day.  After being discharged home, I felt normal, other than some pain in my chest when I would cough or sneeze.   On July 7th, my chest pain became worse.  I was unable to contact my PCP, therefore I went back to the ER.  My troponin levels were normal & was given tramadol and a lidocaine patch for the pain.  Since then I have had a "dull" pain in my right chest, however I have not had to take any medications for this.
LAB_DATA: 6/29/21 - ECG, Chest X-ray, DDimer, Troponin I, CMP, CBC w/diff, Influenza A, Influenza B, COVID-19, POCT Urine Preg Screen, UA w/ Microsocpic, CT Angio Chest with Contrast, Troponin I, CT Head with Contrast, Troponin I, Troponin I 6/30/21 - Troponin I, Magnesium, CBC No Diff, CMP, Echo 7/7/21 - ECG, Xray, Sedimentation rate, CRP High Sensitivity, BNPPATR Peptide, HCG, Troponin I, CMP, CBC w/ Diff, Procalcitonin, Troponin I

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Started experiencing fatigue, muscle weakness.  After light cardio exercise, energy depleted and would have to lie down and then would fall asleep.  I didn't feel sleepy, just extremely weak.  Most pronounced in the arms and legs, but sometimes felt like whole body.  Saw doctor on 5/12.  Later on 6/5 had a complete CBC, physical workup.  Some values were slightly out of range, but nothing significant.  Went to urgent care about a week or so later because symptoms seemed to be getting worse.  They repeated the complete CBC and also ran a lactic acid test.  Again results were insignificant.  Echo completed on 7/1 showing only mild diastolic disfunction.  I'm afraid to exercise.  I wake up in the morning with a mild tingling in hands and legs.  As the morning progresses, the tingling, weakness, fatigue get worse.   I can have some fairly good days, but most are not good.  I have experienced some fatigue in the past, but this time has absolutely been the worse.   Even as I am writing this, I feel the tingling, weakness in my hands.  Earlier my legs felt achy,  Legs feel ok at this time.
