SYMPTOM_TEXT: I received the first dosage of the Moderna vaccine on May 4th of this year.  On May 6th, I had what I term a ?neurological event?.  For several hours, roughly 3, I was so dizzy and nauseous that I couldn?t walk the 20 feet (from living room couch to kitchen) to let my cat in from our deck.  My body temp dropped significantly, I had extreme sensitivity to light and sound, my leg muscles were twitching, my skin was crawling, hands were shaking, and I felt extremely agitated, had difficulty sleeping.  The next day, I had hot flashes, terrible headache, warped vision, dizziness, I was pacing incessantly, and my level of disorientation and confusing was unsettling.  I couldn?t find the right words during conversation, I couldn?t recall small details from one moment to the next, familiar names sounded unfamiliar, I was having trouble following and remembering conversation details, difficulty organizing thoughts, and I was misspelling words that I normally have no trouble with it all, I am an impeccable speller, typically!  My most severe neurological symptoms continued on May 7th and May 8th.  Hot flashes, dry and irritated eyes (feeling like I wanted to claw them out), blurred vision, confusion, headache, and itching skin all continued.  On May 8th, after having a civil conversation with my husband (we are considering moving, I want to move out of the area more than he does, so I was a little frustrated by our conversation) I excused myself to my bedroom, holding my head from this persisting headache, but then suddenly, inexplicably I began screaming and cursing at the top of my lungs and I started to throw my little bottles of acrylic paints down the hallway, until one took an unfortunate left turn and hit the wall, red paint covered the wall and book shelves and carpet, and my emotions quickly turned to sadness and remorse, and I was crying uncontrollably trying to clean it up.  I couldn?t make sense of my extreme behavior, it just wasn?t like me, and the punishment (me throwing paints) didn?t suit the crime (a mildly frustrating conversation).    On May 14th, I had a telehealth visit with my Internist Dr.  (from).  He listened to all of my symptoms and concerns, and I communicated to him that I fear I may have had a seizure or a stroke post vaccine.  The only advice/insight he could offer is that my prescription (my only prescription medication) to treat my anxiety, Viibryd 20 mg once daily, might be the problem.  He asked me to try weaning off of Viibryd, so I followed his advice.  I immediately decreased from 20 mg to 10 mg from May 14th to May 20th.  So May 21st was my first day of no Viibryd, and has continued to be the case since then.  Interestingly, on May 20th, I began to feel intense nerve pain in a spot on my back, to the left of my spine.  I kept asking my husband ?Please tell me what is on my back, is there a bug bite there?? And he promised me over the next few days that there was absolutely nothing there.  On May 23rd, a ?bug bite? and/or rash appeared.  It was the most painful and itchy skin condition I have ever experienced.  The intensity of itching and pain and me clawing at my back, scratching it open, and begging my husband nightly to please ?Get it out of my back, there is something in my back!? continued for a good 2 weeks (please see attached photo) and the area continues to bother me on and off to this day (which I treat with Triamcinolone Acetonide Cream USP, 0.1%, prescribed to me by Dr. , at  urgent care clinic on 6/18.  This is only relief I have received thus far for any of my symptoms). The new set of inflammatory symptoms that accompanied the emergence of this rash/ bug bite are:  Extreme dry and itchy eyes, symptoms escalate in the early evening and are the worst at night (I have a ?few good hours? during the day), fatigue, hot flashes, body feels on fire from the inside, no amount of ice packs and cold showers resolves these symptoms, elevated temperature (my baseline is 97.2 and my temp consistently is 98.1 with this inflammation), marked inflammation and swelling in my hands and legs and body (my rings get stuck on my hands at night, my clothes feel too tight), headaches, my skin hurts/aches, this feels like Mono times 1,000 (I did have Mono 15 years ago), my throat ?glands? are sore and swollen, I have a cyst above my right hip (that I have addressed with my Internist pre-vaccine and he dismissed as nothing) that is so painful and inflamed that I can?t sleep on my right side (which is my preferred side to sleep on), and I have muscle weakness/stiffness in my hands (trouble gripping everyday objects and making a fist).  If I take 2 Alleve (one does nothing) I will get some occasional relief, but even then, Alleve doesn?t always work.  I saw my Internist () on June 8th with this new set of symptoms.  He made it clear from the beginning of my visit that he knew of my 1st visit with Dr. , they had discussed my symptoms.  I tried sharing my notes and new inflammatory symptoms (and did mention and touch upon the unanswered 1st set of neurological symptoms) and was so dismissive of everything I said.  It was very upsetting.  He diagnosed me with stress induced migraines.  I tried explaining to him that I started experiencing migraines in 2nd grade (I am 46 now) and I?ve had both standard and ocular migraines, know what they are like and how to treat them, and they have become much less frequent for me over the years.  I told Tim that these experiences are not migraines.  He insisted they are, and prescribed me Imitrex (without checking my medication allergies in my chart, I am highly allergic to Sulfa/Bactrim.  The pharmacist later alerted me to this).  I stressed my concerns about neurological disorders that run in my family, my Dad is currently perishing from end stages of Alzheimer?s, seizures have begun for him, and we lost his sister in February to Alzheimer?s as well).  I had to beg Tim for appropriate testing, so he conceded to a CT scan for me (of which the results were normal, outside of the previous finding of atherosclerosis of right vertebral artery) and bloodwork (please see attached).  I told  of the rash/bug bite on my back and he refused to look at my photos of it and also refused to look at my back (a bump is still present). I saw  again on 6/17 with the same continuing inflammatory symptoms, and to review my blood work and CT scan.  He said all the tests look great, there is nothing to worry about, it looks like the migraines are resolving.  Again, I told him I am concerned about my continuing symptoms and asked if he thinks I should see a Neurologist and/or a Rheumatologist.  He discouraged me from seeing any specialists, he said the migraines are resolving and the only thing a Rheumatologist is going to tell me is that I might have arthritis in my hands, and there?s nothing more they can do for me.  I informed him of the Imitrex prescription Sulfa allergy oversight, and he seemed surprised, and added Imitrex to my list of medication allergies.  I left the office feeling livid and so discouraged.  I called his office the next day (6/18) to express my frustration and displeasure with how dismissive had been, and I truly feel he is overlooking something serious, perhaps Shingles?  The staff put me on a long hold, and the best they could offer would be for me to see another P.A. the following week (as Dr.  would be on vacation).    I saw a reputable dermatologist, on 6/22, and he dismissed the spot on my back as nothing.

Treated with Benadryl (unclear if at home or in ED) and hydration in ED. Symptoms resolved.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: After getting the 2nd shot, I had no issues other than arm pain. On the 3rd of May, about 3 days later, I started feeling a burning sensation in my chest. The sensation could be felt on the top left of my chest. It was an ongoing feeling. At times I also felt the same sensation at the injection sight. Sometimes there was an achy feeling but the burning was more prominent. On that wednesday, I decided to go to Urgent care as the symptoms did not stop. They had me do a chest xray but did not see any cause for concern and so I was sent home and told to keep an eye on it and that if I had any difficulty breathing or terrible pain in my chest, I should go to the ER. That Saturday, May 8, I went to my doctor's office because I was getting worried and the sensation was not going away. I had begun to feel some chest tightness every now and again. It had now been a week. I was seen by a doctor who said that the vaccine can cause lymph node swelling and that was probably what was happening to me. She felt my chest and arm and said that she could feel swelling. I could feel a bit of swelling in my arm but nowhere else. There were no visible lumps or anything like that. But she said not to worry about it and that it will go away. After another week, I went to my actual doctor for a check up (May 15). After explaining to her what was happening and the anxiety it was causing me, she did an EKG. Results of that were normal and she also did not see any cause for concern. By this time, the sensation had begun to subside. After that day, I did not feel the sensation any more. All and all, the whole ordeal lasted about 2 weeks after getting my second shot

After a few weeks of these daily headaches, I started taking either pain medication at the first sign of an impending headache.   The quality of the headaches were (and continue to be) a dull ache, usually in the back (occipital) of my head and often on the back-right side. Sometimes the ache would be on the sides (parietal) and less often still frontal. No light sensitivity. My physician has diagnosed me and has probably also submitted a VAERS form.   The headaches were daily for at least 6 weeks and I am now getting a break for a day once in a while (maybe 3-4 times). Usually I take Ibuprofen or Acetaminophen daily, so I don't know if a headache would have developed now, so I don't know how regularly they might be coming now, but I did have one 2 days ago and a slight one yesterday despite medication.

LAB_DATA: PE/DVT. Pt presents with increasing SOB, chest tightness for several days. He also noted his BP and HR to be high. He has been complaining of R knee pain recently and thought it was knee arthritis. On presentation he had sinus tachycardia and severe HTN. D dimer was elevated. CT chest showed suboptimal pulmonary artery enhancement. No obvious large emboli. However, there do appear to be subsegmental emboli involving all 5 lobes of both lungs. US leg shows mid and distal right peroneal vein thrombosis. Pt has not needed supplemental O2. Tachycardia has resolved. Echocardiogram did not show R heart strain. He was initially started on heparin drip and then changed to xarelto. There is no obvious cause. He had moderna vaccine a month ago and states he had similar symptoms after the vaccination.     HTN. Very severe at this time. PE and anxiety probably contributing. On lisinopril at home and usually in the 130-140 range systolic at home. We will add amlodipine.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Probably immediately, I was lightheaded and woozy. As soon as she put it in my arm I could taste it and I felt like I was going to vomit. She kept me there for 45 minutes to keep an eye on me. As a disclaimer, I am a vegan and very earthy, I do not take any drugs or anything like that. When I was driving home the lightheadedness got so bad that I had to pull over and sat for 15-20 minutes. I called my brother and he told me to get something to eat. I just had some steamed vegetables. I came home, ate and drank a lot of water to try and get the wooziness to pass. I did not have an unusual amount, no more than I would usually drink. Then after the last bottle of water I had, I started getting more queasy and started to feel dizzy. I then vomited all over my self from head to toe. That lasted for two or three hours and then after that I was dry heaving. That happened on Friday, on Saturday I was too afraid to eat anything I only had toast and a smoothie. On Sunday I was just so woozy and lightheaded and exhausted. I didn't feel chills or anything though. My brother brought me soup on Sunday and I did have some broth. I also started drinking a little bit more water. The water didn't taste good though - it tasted like the vaccine so I did not want to have it. I did not workout at all for that week, I was just so tired. I felt like I could sleep for a month and just not get up. I normally workout five days a week. I got an IV with fluids for hydration and a glutathione push on 7/2/2021. On the following Saturday 7/3/2021, I was still lightheaded. Now, I still am extremely tired and there are days that focusing takes more energy than it typically does. My mouth feels like I have cotton balls in it, the nausea and the lightheadedness is still present, but the tiredness is the worst. I normally run everyday but I cannot even do that at all, walking is hard enough. I just had another IV today 7/14/2021. When this started happening, I did contact my DR but I am unable to get in yet, I need to schedule for a full blood panel and see the DR.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: It was a fully body rash the developed over the course of 24 hours.  The night before I noticed a bit of itching an a bump that seemed like a bug bite. The following morning I had many such bumps in clusters on my neck and arm (and a few more bumps on my legs). At the time I thought I had bed bugs. By about 6 PM, I had more bumps and many of them had spread and turned into welts. There were bumps and rashes on all limbs, my neck and redness on my chest and back, The itchiness was severe. While not extremely painful, it was extremely uncomfortable and seemed like it would be hard to sleep or do anything.  Around 9 PM I took Allegra to try and alleviate symptoms. I also used hydrocortison cream and calamine lotion all over my body to reduce symptoms of itching.  By around 11 PM, I the rash was spreading into my face in the form of some bumps and redness. I visited the ER after consultation with a nurse over the phone, who said that anaphylactic shock could be a possibility and that it would be best to go in.  At the ER, I was treated with 50 mg diphenhydrAMINE , 20 mg famotidine , 10 mg dexAMETHasone. I was given a prescription for dexAMETHasone and instructed to take a refill in 3 days if I still had symptoms. I was discharged a couple hours later.  I did not need to refill the dexAMETHasone  as the sympoms subsided and was almost unnoticeable by day 3 (and completely gone by day 4).
LAB_DATA: A comprehensive metabolic panel was ordered at the ER, because terbinafine can case side effects to the liver. It was found that my liver function was completely normal.  A blood cell count was also taken and everything was normal
OTHER_MEDS: None at time of vaccination.  Was taking terbinafine at time of adverse event (for 29 days).
ALLERGIES: Due to adverse event, we have listed terbinafine as a possible allergy

On 7/8/21, pt had his tooth extracted (#30) at 0930 without complication. At 1200 same day, he received the first dose of the COVID-19 Moderna vaccine. At 1323, the pt was found lying on couch in dorm c/o pain in dental area, dizziness, and lightheadedness (BP 150/77, HR 91, RR 18, O2sat 99%). Heart sounds normal, breath sounds absent on auscultation. Pt was confused and in distress. (unable to respond verbally). His eyes were red and tearing. Tongue and lips appeared red and were mildly swollen. RN was unable to visualize throat in dorm. Epipen was administered at 1340 which resulted in an immediate decrease in symptoms. Pt was calmer and in less distress. Normal uvula with some narrowing of airway noted. He was then taken to clinic and was calm but shaking with an open airway and mild swelling noted; VS wnl. He left via EMS in stable condition to ED at 1400 for evaluation.  Pt returned from ED same day in no acute distress but still c/o dental pain (5/10). He was last evaluated by provider on 7/9/21 and is asymptomatic. Denies swelling, SOB, or fatigue. No bleeding or swelling at dental extraction site noted. Pt evaluated by dental on 7/12/21. No swelling, erythema, exposed bone, or signs of infection noted. Area appears to be following normal post-operative course. Pt remains asymptomatic. SYMPTOM_TEXT: The patient is a 61-year-old male with history of DM type II and hypertension presented to emergency department complaining of generalized weakness and difficulty walking.  Patient stated that he got his second COVID-19 vaccination 2 days ago after which his symptoms started to progressively get worse.  At our facility patient is noted to be febrile, dehydrated, and tachycardic requiring oxygen.  His COVID-19 test is negative.  He is compliant with his home medications.  He tolerated his first COVID-19 vaccine without any complications.  He did have COVID-19 infection in March, 2021 and recovered without complications at home with over counter medications.    61-year-old who states that he has become weaker and unable to ambulate for the past 2 weeks.  Denies any chest pain.  Denies any cough sputum production.  He has not had any fever rigors or chills.. Received the Covid vaccine second dose 2 days ago but states that he these problems for approximately 2 years or so.  He had a coronary angiogram at USC at that time.  He states that he was told to take Coreg spironolactone and bumetanide.  He is a never smoker.  States that he stopped alcohol many years ago.    Assessment/Plan  1. Cardiogenic shock   Echo shows EF of 10% 2. Cardiomyopathy  3. Anasarca   Discharge summary: Hospital Course       61 years old male with past medical history of cardiomyopathy and chronic systolic congestive heart failure, history of diabetes and hypertension who presented to the emergency room complaining generalized weakness and difficulty ambulating, patient states that he received his second dose of Covid 19 vaccine 2 days prior to his symptoms, patient started to get weak and his symptoms got progressively worse, on arrival to the emergency room patient was found to have a fever of 38.2 was tachycardic and tachypneic as well requiring oxygen, his COVID-19 test in the emergency room was negative per patient when he received his first Covid vaccine was without any complication at that time patient was given 2 L of fluids in the emergency room and our team was consulted to admit the patient, patient also was noted to be hypoglycemic in the emergency room and his hyperglycemia worsen and became hypotensive at that time I evaluated the patient he was responsive and able to open his eyes and follow simple command, patient was started on Levophed drip and ICU was called for admission given patient instability, he had an echo that showed left ventricular ejection fraction of about 10% and patient was admitted to the ICU, patient continued on antibiotics for possible pneumonia and UTI and had paracentesis done after the procedure patient had a CODE BLUE and he was intubated with return of pulse and blood pressure although he had another code at that time ICU discussed with the family given his comorbidity and poor prognosis given patient had 2 cardiac arrest and family requested for the patient to be do not escalate and patient was pronounced dead at 21:47

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Instant headache and pain shooting down arm and side while being injected, sick feeling and light headed right as I was leaving the facility.  Within 4 hours I was struggling to do anything.  I was tired and felt and nauseated, light headed and felt like i was hit by a truck.  The bottoms of my feet hurt and I had stabbing pains so bad in my knee joints I could barely walk without assistance.  I felt very ill for about a week after the shot but the headaches continued constantly for over a month but aren't daily anymore even though I still have them, and the fatigue was getting worse and still is a problem to this day. Once I was feeling a bit better my right knee started to give out and my left knee was cracking. Since I got that vaccine on 3/6/21 I have had back to back problems.  Below is a quick list of these things that have occurred by dates: 3/30/21 - Constant headaches since the vaccine and ear pain and throat issues.  4/16/21 - Right knee giving out on me that started shortly after vaccine and gotten worse.  X-ray and physical therapy ordered.  4/22/21 - Shortness of breath, back pain, constant fatigue.  Blood work that showed elevated D-dimer then chest x-ray and ct-scan ordered. 4/26/21 - Ultrasound for nodule found on ct-scan. 5/4/21 - Biopsy done of mediastinal mass. 5/11/21 - Physical done for surgery. 5/24/21 - Surgery to remove mediastinal mass, right side of thyroid, two parathyroids and lymph nodes. 6/1/21 - Follow-up for surgery.  When I asked why this happened, the doctor said we may never know but the biopsy of the right thyroid nodule result showed thyroiditis, Autoimmune/Hashimoto's, and  that my immune system attacked my thyroid.  The doctor said she tested me for that in 9/20 and it was negative. 6/2/21 - Left knee pain.  About 4 days after my surgery on 5/24 i turned towards the door and heard a loud pop in my left knee.  It had been crackling since the vaccine but wasn't giving out like the right one. I couldn't walk on it at all and was using crutches.   6/9/21 - Mri on left knee showed medial and lateral meniscus tears.  Referred to Ortho Dr. 6/28/21 - Test thyroid levels post op.  TSH levels high.  Referral to Endocrinologist. 6/30/21 - Left knee treatment, cortisone shot in knee for now to help with pain and inflammation so I can function and physical therapy.  Since then my 4th toe on my right foot has been numb for almost two weeks.  I am scheduled for numerous future physical therapy appointments and doctors appointments.    Then to make matters worse I just heard 2 days ago that J&J is having more issues and mentioned autoimmune and wondered could that be what caused all of this?   I regret getting that stupid J&J vaccine.  I expected it to he the Pfizer because that is what was there 2 days before I got my shot.  I told the person I didn't want it and she got someone in charge to talk me into it.  I should have walked out of there and I am mad at myself for caving to this woman.  If J&J says we need a booster I will refuse to take it.  I don't know if the vaccine was what triggered all of this but I find it quite odd that all of this started almost immediately after I got that vaccine.  Not only to me but also to my sister who got it at the same time.  She fell within 30 minutes of getting that vaccine and 3 more times that day, and has had and is still having numerous problems that mimic mine, such as issues with her feet and legs.  She struggles to walk and is having issues with her thyroid among other things that she wasn't having a problem with prior to the vaccine. This is just the short version of all I have been through.  Any questions feel free to contact me.

Likely exophytic single or confluent thyroid nodules. Consider thyroid ultrasound for evaluation. 4/26/21 - Ultrasound - Multinodular goiter with 4.3 cm thyroid nodule at midline inferior to the thyroid lobes corresponding to lesion seen on recent chest CT and with features meeting criteria for biopsy. 5/4/21 - Biopsy done showed benign thyroid tissue in chest and scheduled surgery for removal. 5/25/21 - Surgical biopsy's of tissues removed are all benign but not normal tissue.  Too much info to try to put here. 6/9/21 - MRI left knee - medial and lateral meniscus tears. 6/28/21 - thyroid testing 30 days post op - high TSH levels. 6/30/21 - X-ray left knee - abnormal results but not in the online portal to tell you what they were.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: During first episode, patient experienced sudden-onset shortness of breath, tachycardia, and heart palpitations. Patient promptly visited the emergency room where multiple EKGs were recorded and heart rate was measured in the 150-160 range resting. Patient was given IV metoprolol to slow heart rate. Patient then followed up with primary care provider and was given a Holter monitor to wear for 48 hours and received a referral to a cardiologist. Patient then attended appointment with cardiologist who provided her with a 30 day heart monitor. Two days later, patient experienced another episode that caused her to visit the emergency room again. After being discharged, patient continued to experience episodes of tachycardia, shortness, or breath, and palpitations coupled with  dizziness, fatigue, and hypotension. Patient made another visit to her primary care provider due to more frequent episodes and constant dizziness with hypotension. Primary care provider suspects supraventricular tachycardia and orthostatic hypotension and prescribed Midodrine to patient to raise blood pressure and combat dizziness.

I got the vaccine, and within a couple of days, I started having chills, fatigue, nausea, muscle and body aches, and headaches. It got continually worse, and I eventually developed a migraine, blurred vision, tingling, severe nose bleeds, weakness (like peripheral neuropathy). The symptoms all got worse and worse, and I eventually went to the neurologist. They did a CT venogram; the results were normal. The BP was elevated, and they noted I had a really high heart rate. My blood work had abnormalities on the CBC and metabolic panels. I was sent back to my PCP and he found abnormal results in my blood work, plus he found abnormalities in the test for thyroid stimulating hormone. I still had elevated BP. A PCR COVID test was done, and I tested negative. They also tested for antibodies to see if I was responding to the vaccine; no antibodies were detected. They said it was weird and that I probably had lingering vaccine side effects that would go away, and in case the COVID test was wrong, I was advised to self-isolate. They plan to conduct further thyroid tests and blood work in the future to see if there are any changes. I am still having all the symptoms, and on 7/13/2021, I developed symptoms that are consistent either kidney stones or kidney infection. I plan to see my doctor to have this looked into.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I decided to sit for 30 mins after the 2nd vaccine. At about 15 minutes after the vaccine, I was lightheaded, and my heart started to beat bad. I also had extreme chest pain. They took my vitals and I started to sweat profusely. Based on my vitals and my symptoms they thought I was having a heart attack. They took me over to the ER, and I started to experience kidney pain. The pain from that was so bad I thought I was going to vomit. They took me back into one of the rooms and they started all the test to see if I was having a heart attack. I started to have trouble breathing. My pulse was okay. All the tests came back inconclusive. My EKG came back abnormal. They discharged me to go home. I went back to the ER less than a week later because I was experiencing COVID like symptoms. I was tachycardic and had hard time breathing. I had swelling in my arm where the injection was given. I was unable to dress like normal and I could not even walk my dog without being out of breath. I went to the Urgent Care and they diagnosed me with a Pleurisies' and System Inflammatory. They prescribed me a steroid and I was told to take it for 10 days. They also gave me an inhaler as well. They did not do anything. I went back to the doctor after the steroid, and I was still having difficulty breathing. I had joint pain, headaches, I was still unable to take a deep breath. I was sitting at my kitchen table and passed out. I woke up on the floor. I drove myself to the ER and they were going to admit me, and they treated me for a migraine. They decided to a migraine cocktail. I had extreme pain in my lower legs. They were afraid of me having a DVT. They did an ultrasound and did not find a DVT. They decided to send me home. Between the last visit to now I have had between 5-7 more visits to the ER and urgent care due to not being able to breath and the joint pain. I have Dilated Aortic Root Valve and I am also Tachycardic neither of which I had before. Now I am better, but I do at times have difficulty breathing.
LAB_DATA: EKG x2

I woke up Friday morning and my right arm felt like ice cold water was dripping down (but wasn?t). My husband took my blood pressure and it was really high and my chest felt tight. Given that the vaccine was just paused for blood clots we went to the ER. They ran labs and said I didn?t have any clots.  Here is the timeline of what happened after:  Saturday & Sunday & Monday: Felt normal again  Tuesday: Felt short of breath  Tingles started to come back  Wednesday: Leg and arm numbness   Thursday thru the next few days were the worst:  Thursday: Random sharp pains, back, thigh, ab  Right calf felt a bit swollen and more sensitive  Tingling on back of head Tingling in leg and arm  High anxiety pain in chest  No appetite High blood pressure   Friday: Muscle twitching in thigh, sides and random places  Random tightness/sharp pain in thigh  Blood pressure and heart rate went back to normal  High anxiety pain in chest before bed  Didn?t sleep well keep panicking awake (not normal) No appetite   Saturday: Right calf slightly swollen after walking around  Still had muscle twitches and it?s always in the same spot in my thigh   Did a teledoc appt which was totally unhelpful  High anxiety pain in chest- felt like I was going to pass out at one point and we took my blood pressure in that moment and it was high ?happened after dinner No appetite  Note: anxiety is not something I?ve ever had   Sunday: Swelling in leg returned Sharp pains randomly A little heavy to breath at times  Tension in my head ? felt cold After I ate dinner chest heaviness returned Sensory overload- watching tv couldn?t do. It wasn?t until I got a small cold that the tingling flared up again. Right leg continues to be a problem-tingling and numbness comes and goes daily. I?ve also had a few episodes of chest tightness out of the blue.  Last night I woke up to find my right arm also tingly and numb.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: On June, 9, 2021, the day after I received the 2nd dose of the Moderna vaccine, I experienced intense pain in my left arm.  I expected pain in my arm again since that is how it felt the first time.  The pain felt as if someone punched me extremely hard, leaving me feeling like I needed a sling to support the injury.  The pain in my left arm felt had a throbbing, pulsing, almost numbing feel all on the outside and although it did feel a little different than the first time, I figured it would get better like after the first vaccine I received on May 11, 2021.   Other symptoms I experienced were: waxing and waning low-grade fevers all day, severe fatigue and brain fog, dizziness,  little appetite, shakiness, rapid breathing and then shallow breathing (in line with my heart pounding or slowing down), and nausea. The symptoms were familiar to me, and it felt like deja vu but a milder version of when I had Covid-19 in August 2020.  As a reference to what I will mention next, when I had Covid-19 last year I developed subacute thyroiditis from the acute respiratory virus, and this was supported by a blood test.  My levels appeared to be normal going into the vaccine, and since I never have had thyroid challenges the past I didn't expect to have fluctuating hormones post Covid or post-vaccine.   As of now, July 14, 2021, I still am experiencing some of the milder symptoms on occasion (brain fog, dizziness, shakiness), and the hormone regulation has been a bit off too.  My left arm has a dull ache/pain and numbness the starts at the vaccine site in my shoulder down the outside of the arm, pulses pain in my left wrist, and stops at the last two fingers on my left hand.  As far as I can tell, I do have full range of motion and can still exercise.  My recovery time is slower and the tingling feeling doesn't subside, and if anything it increases randomly.  I was hoping the dull ache and numb feeling would subside by this point, but it hasn't.  My best guess is that I have neurological damage in my left arm, and I have a long term recovery in my hormonal health.
PRIOR_VAX: Extreme Pain in Left arm

SYMPTOM_TEXT: May not be related but I'm not a fan of "coincidence". 8-10 hours after 2nd shot, right pinky & ring finger started feeling numb and not moving normally.  The next morning, those 2 fingers were completely numb and I could not type or write.  The following day, I could feel those 2 fingers but they would not move normally.  There was also a loss of strength such that I was unable to expand my fingers -- such as what you do when opening a pair of closed scissors.  I had to move those 2 fingers with my other hand if I wanted to expand them.  During the following week, the symptoms improved slowly.  By week #2, I could type again but still had some weakness and my hand, wrist, arm tired easily.  At the 3 week mark, I saw an Orthopedic specialist (because I made the appointment the day I couldn't move my fingers) and he had no real explanation.  He said the symptoms I described normally progress the opposite way...starting subtle and progressing to loss of hand/finger function.  Starting with loss of hand/finger function and then it getting better slowly was not something he had seen.  No real treatment or known cause of the problem.  The Orthopedic specialist told me to wear a brace and call if it happens again.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I felt heart palpitations, which prompted me to check my heart rate using my electronic device. It was an uncomfortable feeling in my chest. During the 2 days following vaccination, I came down with a high fever. I took Tylenol. So I thought my higher heart rate was due to my body fighting off the fever. SYMPTOM_TEXT: On April 18, 2021 I woke up with severe vertigo which I had never had before it lasted approximately 16 hours. Then on April 28, 2021 I became very uncoordinated, slurred speech, depth perception was off a lot of neuropathic pain something just wasn?t right. Was check to make sure I wasn?t having a stroke, and I followed up with my primary care. For seven days I couldn?t drive I couldn?t walk without assistance and my whole world was in just an upside down moment. My primary care physician ordered an MRI and a ton of bloodwork to see if it was possibly MS. The MRI came back negative with a normal brain scan but my blood work came back positive for neuromyelitis optica  NMO for short. I have never had a history of any form of autoimmune disease. Demyelinating disease nothing like that. My whole world is literally shattering around me because now I?ve been diagnosed with this NMO, And trying to find a provider that can possibly help me with such a very rare autoimmune disorder. The more I read about the COVID-19 vaccine I think the Covid vaccine has caused this rare disorder and I?m scared to death I don?t want anyone else to have to go through this.
LAB_DATA: MRI brain, Cervical spine, T-spine, Lumbar, numerous serum tests and 2 positive NMO IgG antibodies results

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 1. My period, which I got on April 20th (18 days after dose 2), resulted in extreme and debilitating cramps, which are lasting to this day. They're so bad I can't get out of bed for the first two days of my period - then I have infrequent occasional pangs of pain on day 3, and I'm okay days 4 and 5. I have never had cramps during my cycle before April 2021.   2. On April 16th, I was driving my car and I noticed that when I had my foot on the the brake, it was shaking uncontrollably in almost every position I put my leg in. The frequency of this leg tremor during driving became more frequent, and I started noticing heightened anxiety, trouble focusing, weight loss of 7 pounds thus far (my weight has not fluctuated more then 3 pounds in the last 4 years so this was a surprise to me), lightened period, increased heat intolerance, heart palpitations that keep me awake at night and tachychardia, muscle weakness, and fatigue. I had a really stressful semester in school so I chalked these symptoms up to anxiety.  Then, in the first week of June, I went to the gynecologist to get the cramps situation checked out. She told me she wanted me to check out my thyroid for the rest of the symptoms. When my blood test came back, my Thyroid Stimulating Hormone (TSH) result came back as 0.03 (lowest acceptable range is 0.4). My primary care provider ran T3 and T4 tests, which came back as 15 and 5, respectively - which are both quite elevated for their range. So, I went to an endocrinologist at my primary care provider's referral, who ran more tests. This time, they found TSH to be 0.006 (got lower), T3 and T4 were elevated, very slightly lower than they were before. My endocrinologist then ran a test for Thyroglobulin antibody, which came back as 53.3, when the highest reference value was 0.9. Thus, my endocrinologist determined hyperthyroidism, but wanted to figure out the what I had so she sent me for a thyroid uptake scan. In the scan, they found my thyroid to be working at 51%, when the highest value after 24 hours of receiving the radioactive iodine was 33%, and my endocrinologist determined that I had Graves' Disease, an autoimmune hyperthyroid disease.   I am now on Methimazole and Propranolol for Graves' Disease.   I don't know if the vaccine caused my horrendously painful cramps and the onset of the autoimmune disease, but I just wanted the CDC to know! I am curious to know if there is a correlation.  Please let me know if you have any questions.
LAB_DATA: Blood tests, thyroid ultrasound, thyroid uptake scan - all in June.
OTHER_MEDS: Vitamin C, Vitamin D, Calcium, Biotin, Allegra

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I got my shot. It lightly sting nothing bad.  - About 40 min later on both sides of my back I felt tingling right below my shoulder blades  and then this spread out like a waterfall going down my back .  - about an hour later it was like someone turned my power off. I was so tired I could barely open the car door and walk inside - laid down and slept maybe 3 hours ? - woke up hurting and puking  - hot and cold and exhausted  - slept next day . Not hungry but husband bright oatmeal and coffee. I ate a bite and threw it all up  - my body get like it had become broken glass . It hurt . It hurt to walk to the kitchen . My eyelashes hurt , my nails hurt . Stayed in bed. Ate a TV dinner and threw it up . Feverish . Sweating hot cold . Felt like a migraine headache I guess around my forehead and eyes - and I have never had one .  - day 3 - nauseous. Took shower and big clumps of my hair fell out . Feet hurt and tingled. Felt like a spike gong through my right side off and on .   Day 4 - slept all day and had to drive 8 hours home.  My left eye hurt and was draining . When I got home I looked in the mirror and the left side of my face was swollen really badly and eye about swollen shut. Felt bad . Achy and stabbing side pain .  Went to Urgent Er care due to  face  swelling .  They had no explanation .  Had a cyst like pimple on left side under eye that went back up to eye lid   Could not turn my neck and really sore . Went to Chiropractor doctor. He and his assistant examined me and said I was not out of alignment but my lymph nodes around my neck area and left side of my spleen were very swollen .  He said to go to dentist over face swelling and I probably had an infected tooth   Went to dentist . Teeth were fine but he said to go to the eye doctor .  Still feeling sick and very achy . Hurt to walk . Knees hurt . Felt like I was 100 years old   Went to eye doctor .   He examined my eye then had me go to another room and machine . Then a variety of students came in to look at my eye . I asked why and one said because they only read about this in text book. Doctor came bAck and said I had acute narrow angle eye closure and had to do emergency surgery .  Still feel horrible   Labs now coming back with odd things . Doctor sending me to rheumatoid / endocrinologist and integrative doc but can?t get appointments til  October    Now have holes in my iris to relieve the pressure and other auto immune things going on . Doctor said tissue swelled on optic nerve . Saw glitter like out of side  of eye . He said I?d loose my eyesight if I did not have the emergency surgery
LAB_DATA: Yes  Urgent care  Chiropractor Doctor  Dentist  Lots and lots of blood work  Optometrist  and emergency eye surgery

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Pt was give two doses of VARCELLA It was brought to my attention that nurse gave the wrong vaccine to patient. The patient and dad was already gone when nurse told me. She said that she pulled a varivax and what she thought was an MMR and drew them up and gave them Bralie. So she received a combination MMR/Varicella and a Varivax. I immediately called the dad and told him what had happened. I also contacted hospital and reported the mistake. I asked for any side effects that we should look for in patient. I was told that the research showed that the greatest risk with this situation is febrile seizures and recommended that the patient take Tylenol every 4 hours for the next 24 hours. I spoke with Dad again and gave him the information and gave very strong er warnings. Dad verbalized understanding of all. I informed our supervising physician and told him of the incident. Parents were called 3 hours after the incident and again today. Patient has not run a fever and has been playing, eating, and drinking well. Will continue to monitor progress.   Lot numbers of the vaccines: Varicella Lot #7024284 Exp 7-15-2022 Proquad Lot # 7027115 Exp 2-7/2022
LAB_DATA: none

She says she does not feel she can fully empty her bladder despite having urgency to do so. She denies gross hematuria. She says she does not feel well in general and has no energy. She feels her flank pain is becoming worse and Tylenol is no longer giving her relief. Her brother says the family wanted to ensure there was no complications involving her kidneys considering her history.  The renal team did not feel patients symptoms were related to a kidney/bladder issue but rather a reaction to her second COVID vaccine. Her case was discussed with rheumatology and infectious disease. She received ondansetron for nausea, Naproxen for pain, and encouraged her to remain well hydrated. She was  prescribed a short course of prednisone.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: The patient has not had any side effects outside of the typical response expected from the Janssen vaccine. However, the error occurred due to the fact that the vial the vaccine was drawn up from was opened the day prior (Tuesday, 7/13/21 at roughly 2pm), which has a BUD of 6 hours in the refrigerator after it is punctured. The pharmacist who administered the vaccine wasn't aware that the vial had been punctured the day prior and not the day the vaccine was actually administered, which was Wednesday, 7/14/21 at 10:38am.  The patient has been made aware of the situation and is currently not experiencing any negative or out of the ordinary side effects. He was informed to contact us if he begins to. Due to the lack of data/studies on whether or not the patient should receive another dose of the vaccine, the patient has elected to not receive another dose and has accepted the potential the vaccine may not be as effective as the CDC has described due to it being administered past it's BUD. The manufacturer of Janssen has been notified of the error as well. Vials will now be disposed of at the end of each work day in order to prevent another error like this from occurring again.
LAB_DATA: No medical tests or laboratory results were needed.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: On Friday night I had increased heart rate and couldn't catch my breath. The ambulance came and did an EKG where everything was normal. They took me to the ER. When I got there, they wheeled me out into the waiting area. While I was there, I was sitting there for about 2-3 hours. I noticed that my heart rate was not spiking anymore, and my breathing was better. I asked to be discharged without being seen. On 4/19, I went to pick up my daughter after a walk. When I got back, I was gasping for air and had chest pain. I went to the ER where they told me I had an elevated D dimer. They referred me to a cardiologist. They did all the CT scans and said they did not see anything, so they discharged me. On 4/14 I saw the cardiologist, who said he does not think it was due to pericardial effusion/pericarditis which I was diagnosed with after the birth of my daughter in June 2019. He had done an echo which was normal in October. I also saw my PCP where my blood pressure medication was changed to amlodipine and I was referred to a pulmonologist. I saw doctor who did a bunch of tests and did not find anything. He suggested I had costochondritis and put me on Toradol and an asthma pump. The asthma pump did not help. On 5/7, I had extreme chest pain where I could not move my arm. I went to the ER where they did a scan of my heart to check for fluid and a D dimer test. Since receiving the shot, I noticed my tonsils would swell up after eating. I had to stop eating and went on an ensure diet. I went to an allergist that said I was severely allergic to rice, a dog, but I was never allergic to anything before. I went back to the cardiologist where the PA said even though there is nothing wrong, maybe there is unseen myocarditis or pericarditis. The medication messed with my stomach. I went to check that everything was fine with my lungs where everything was deemed fine. On 5/27, I did a stress test which was fine. On 6/2, I had experienced shortness of breath again. I was unable to work normally and had to stop working. Doctor did tests for inflammatory diseases Mitochondrial M2 antibodies was in the middle range. This is inconclusive. I went to doctor who ran a lot of tests and found that Sedimentation rate was too high, Comprehensive metabolic rate was normal, CMV Igg: positive. He said perhaps I have long haul COVID. The antibody test showed I was positive for the vaccine antibodies but not the true COVID antibody. He suggested it could be an inflammatory issue. I saw an ENT for my throat who put me on antibiotics. The antibiotics helped but when I got off, I had another flare up. I was put on more antibiotics. On 6/29, I went to another cardiologist who did a contact MRI. He saw a swollen left atrium but said it was overall normal. I also saw a pulmonologist to notify them that the shortness of breath is still sometimes present. I saw a GI who did a test and found that I had erosive gastritis. I was taking metoprolol and tarivid. I still have stomach discomfort.
LAB_DATA: Stress test, Holter, EKG, CT, MRI, Echo, Inflammatory diseases test.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: No immediate adverse reaction, however, began developing nightly fevers/profuse sweating on June 11.  This continued for two weeks with increasing symptoms of loss of appetite, nausea, abdominal pain, tingling sensation on scalp before going to ER.  Visited urgent care on June 16 and bloodwork results indicated elevated white blood cell count and eosinophil count.  There was a question as to whether patient had been subjected to a tick bite, so doxycycline was prescribed.  After several days, patient returned to urgent care for follow-up bloodwork (June 20th).  Results showed WBC and eosinophil count continued to escalate.  He went to ER on June 25th and was admitted to the hospital for 5 days.  During his visit at Hospital, he was seen by a team of specialists:  cardiologist, pulmonologist, hematologist, infectious disease doctor.  Multiple tests were run, as the doctors started broad to eliminate certain diagnoses - i.e., bone marrow biopsy, heart cath, CT scans, x-rays, thoracentesis, etc.  Patient had fluid around his heart and lungs and was diagnosed with myocarditis.  He had no previous heart issues nor family history of heart issues.  Test results indicated no abnormal  blockage or other issues, other than inflammation and his heart strength was at 27%.  I am unable to access his account, as it was disabled after his death.  An autopsy is being performed and results are pending; however, the question(s) at large:  what was the condition of his heart at the time of his death and was this vaccine-related?  Did his myocarditis get worse?  Did his heart muscle weaken further and rupture?    Please let me know if the autopsy results are needed and where to send them.
OTHER_MEDS: Dulera, Albuterol, Multi-Vitamin, Ubiquinol, Vitamin D

Beginning 1 week after the shot, my toes turned purple; this has continued on and off since May 5, 2021.  Beginning 2 weeks after the shot, the lymph nodes in my neck, roof of my mouth, nose, and ears were swollen and tender. At random times, I would get hot and begin to sweat profusely 2-3 times per day, and my ears would get extremely red. At this time, my temperature would be between 100F and 101F, and my blood pressure was elevated. These symptoms lasted about 4 weeks.  Beginning 3 weeks after the shot, I developed a walnut-sized, squishy knot on the inside of the joint of my left elbow. I also began losing the hair in my armpits and have since completely lost all the hair in my armpits and on my legs.   Beginning 4 weeks after the shot, I developed a golf-ball-sized, squishy knot on the inside of my right knee, similar to the one that appeared on my elbow. I also developed a walnut-sized, squishy knot on my left knee just below the kneecap.  Beginning 5 weeks after the shot, I developed shin splints but had not completed any running or other activities that could explain the tenderness in my shins.  Beginning 6 weeks after the shot, I noticed a loss of muscle mass in my arms and legs.   Beginning 7 weeks after the shot, I have had severe chest pain three times. Each felt like I was having a heart attack; 2 times were in the middle of the night and 1 time was early in the morning.   Beginning 8 weeks after the shot, I began getting lightheaded at random which has caused me to fall multiple times. In addition, I have begun bruising very easily; the bruises take weeks to heal. My left eye is also extremely tender and waters more than normal.   Beginning 9 weeks after the shot, I notice that I have begun drooling even though I have never drooled in the past. My gums occasionally feel tender when I brush my teeth.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Received shot Tuesday July 6. On Thursday July 8 at 11pm I woke up with a terrible case of itching . I put on Cortisone cream 1% and the itching stopped.  Went back to bed and a hour later was woke up with more bumps itching put on cream this went on the rest of the night.  Got up around 3am Friday and they were all gone.  I had no problems until 4pm Friday and the bumps came back.  Friday night was like Thursday night.  Saturday got up all gone,  I went to Urgent Care and saw a Dr.  who told me I was one out of a hand full to react this way to the shot.  He told me to continue with the cream and take 12.5 mg of Benadryl.  Saturday at 4pm a few bumps appeared so I put the cream on them and took the  Benadryl.  I was not woken up by the bumps all Saturday night.  Got up Sunday all gone.  Sunday, Monday and Tuesday evening I took the Benadryl with no bumps. Last night Wednesday July 14 I did not take the Benadryl and had no problems.   Tuesday I did see my Primary Care Doctor about whether I should receive the second shot.  I said this is all to new to give me an answer told me to contact CDC for an answer.   Should I receive the Second Shot as scheduled on August 3

SYMPTOM_TEXT: patient received J & J vaccine at 1050 am  patient was talking with nurse and suddenly stiffened his body with clenching fists curled upward to chest.  He had bright red skin color, and could not speak.  this lasted 10 seconds at most.  Afterward the patient was sitting in chair had turned very pale and did not realize what had happened.  one of the other nurses asked him if he knew where he was, he stated "In the Hospital", the nurse repeated that he was not in hospital, that he was at the health department getting a Covid shot.  He stated "oh yeah.. I forgot,"  patient stated he was going to be sick,  patient grabbed garbage can that was sitting next to him Patient was hooked up to oximetry, reading was 99% on RA, attempted Blood pressure 3 times but was unable to attain a reading, patient was holding garbage can tightly.  patient had emesis 3x's that was clear in color, cold packs were placed on the nape of the neck and under armpit, patient was sweating and white in color.  patient stated he had blurred vision, and noted that he was unconscious for approx. 25-30 seconds.  911 was called at 10:57.  Nursing supervisor was notified at 10:58. Patient stated that he had nothing to eat today, and his mother stated that he had been anxious about getting the vaccine and that she made her son get it.  Epinephrine was available but not given.  no issues with breathing.  EMS came in did a quick evaluation and transported patient to the hospital.  Mother was with patient during the entire incident.
LAB_DATA: unknown

LAB_DATA: N/A...I just decided to report these symptoms and am hoping they go away, naturally. I figure the ears ringing are a result of swelling which may be a side effect.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 1/11/21: neck and shoulder stiffness and arthritis-like pain starts and continues until Prednisolone dose pack 4/28/21.  Stiffness and pain resumes in May-July but not as bad. 1/17/21: one week after 1st vaccine see large (egg size) swelling at injection site that lasts a few days. 1/20/21: numbness and tingling in right hand, especially in mornings. Much worse if I sleep on side.  1/28/21: Saw Chiropractor, thinking I had pinched nerve in neck (previous MRI showed disk bulges at C5-6 and C6-C7). Numbness and symptoms continue. Heat or ice no help.  Must sleep flat on back with no pillow to prevent numbness/tingling.  2/27: 2nd Moderna vaccine, little swelling.   Stiffness in neck/shoulder continues.  Numbness and tingling start in left hand as well as right.  3/10/21: Saw Dr. (Orthopedic Surgeon), prescribed Gabapentin and PT. Gabapentin no help,  PT including traction to stretch neck,  and new exercises temporarily help with neck stiffness and numbness and tingling, but symptoms return.  3/27 Hands (BOTH) and fingers extremely stiff and bent in morning, painful and difficult to flex. Never had arthritis in hands previously. 4/7/21: televisit with (PCP), recommended RA test (negative) and prescribed Tizanidine (helps me get to sleep). Recommended follow up with neurologist (MS). March-July: arthritis symptoms in hands every norming, numbness and tingling in fingers almost continuous. Noticable increased pain in knees when squatting.  4/24: some numbness and tingling in butt and feet when laying down flat.  4/28/21: Saw my neurologist (Dr.) out of concern that these were new MS symptoms. ( I had stopped taking Betaseron in December 2020). Recommended MRI of head and neck, which showed no new lesions indicative of MS exacerbation. Prescribed dose pack of Prednisolone which helped relieve stiffness and pain in neck and shoulders (it returns later, but not as bad). Recommended EMG.  6/18/21: Saw Milvia Yadira Pleitez, for EMG which indicated bilateral carpal tunnel syndrome.  6/22/21 Saw Dr.  EMG shows sensory and auto nerves affected on R hand, sensory only on left hand. Wear wrist braces for 12 weeks, then steroid shots if necessary, then surgery.  Knee xray shows no abnormalities.  Physical therapy for knee available.  Arthritis in hands/knee may be related to COVID vaccine.  6/22-7/10: Taking Naproxen about every other night, muscle relaxant only when stiff.  Neck and shoulder better but still stiff. Can sleep on side for limited time.  Fingers still numb, no improvement with hand braces.  Hand pain and stiffness in a.m. Knee pain when squatting continues.

I decided to go back on my Prednisone (I had gotten off of it for taking both doses of the vaccine). I had to take Prednisone for about a month to help with my polymyalgia symptoms. That pretty much too care of it but I took Tylenol and Advil to manage the symptoms after that. My arm continued to be sore. During the whole time, I had a frozen shoulder (since right after the vaccine). Frozen shoulder is just on the one side (which is on area of the vaccination). It wasn't working - or getting better. I called my doctor and went in to see her end of May. I waited a couple of weeks and my shoulder became more frozen. My doctor got me into physical therapy which I have been doing for the past month. I continue to take Tylenol and Advil to manage the symptoms. They polymyalgia symptoms are mostly gone. Just  have some residual stuff but it's going away. As a side note: I have had reactions to vaccines that are a little unusual - that have lasted from 3 days to 3 months (in the past).  I'm about 60% recovered from the frozen shoulder.

On the evening of Friday, April 16th, 2021, I experienced increased body temperature, chills, severe nausea. I completed COVID-19 testing on 4/17/21 (both rapid test and PCR test were negative). I continued to experience persistent elevated body temperature (although not true fever), periods of warmth, chills, recurrent headaches (frontal), exhaustion, burping, more pale looking, and periods of lightheadedness (when at work and home, regardless of what I was doing). I scheduled a 'sick' visit with my primary care physician, completing a telehealth visit (per my MD) on 4/27/21 due to the aforementioned symptoms. I received a blood pressure monitor free through my health insurance and began taking my blood pressure at the beginning of May. My blood pressure during the first two weeks of May was averaging 95/62 (with peak blood pressure reading of 107/65) with my blood pressure cuff identifying irregular heartbeats on 5/6/21, 5/11/21, 5/12/21.  Although some symptoms resolved, I continued to experience periods of lightheadedness, chest pain/pressure in the middle of my chest, and soft blood pressure readings.  I saw my rheumatologist on 5/12/21 (who also documented a low blood pressure reading in office and wrote an order for an ECHO). I completed a telehealth visit with my GI, who advised to continue use of pantoprazole and increased PRN use of sucralfate. I continued to experience increasingly more frequent instances of lightheadedness, increasing chest pain/pressure, and my blood pressure continued to decrease. I was 'strongly advised' by my primary care MD's office to seek cardiac workup at an Emergency Room on 5/18/21. I presented to the Emergency Department on 5/18/21 at approximately 1330 and was discharged from the ED at approximately 3:30am on 5/19. I was advised to complete my already scheduled ECHO (scheduled and completed on 5/25/21), to seek the care of a cardiologist, and follow-up with my primary care MD.  I saw a NP  who is part of my primary MD's office on 5/20/21. I saw cardiologist on 5/27/21, who advised me to hydrate with liberal use of salt (due to persistent low blood pressure readings, documented during my in-person office visit). I completed a stress test on 6/18/21.  Due to persistent low blood pressure, my cardiologist started me on midodrine 5mg tablets twice a day and ordered a Ziopatch cardiac monitor to be worn for 5 days. I was advised by my cardiologist to see an endocrinologist as he is unable to identify the cause of my low blood pressure.  At the time of writing, I continue to experience low blood pressure, periods of lightheadedness, occasional chest pain/pressure in center of chest, and periods of increased fatigue.
LAB_DATA: -Labwork drawn/completed on 4/27/21 (due to sick visit) -Labwork ordered by rheumatologist (completed on 5/12/21) -Labwork completed during Emergency Department visit on 5/18-5/19 -Bedside ECHO, EKG, Chest X-ray  completed during ED visit on 5/18-5/19 -ECHO (completed on 5/25/21, ordered by rheumatologist) -EKG completed at cardiologist's office on 5/27/21 -Stress Test completed at cardiologist's office on 6/18/21 -ZioPatch Cardiac Monitor (worn from evening of 6/28/21-morning of 7/6/21)

On May 8th, I was at my grandchild's football game. I was outside for over 3 hours. It was a very windy day, and I had a lot of coffee. In the evening, I went to my grandchild's concert at school at 7:00PM. While at the concert, my neck started throbbing and I started getting a headache. When the concert ended, I started having trouble walking back to the vehicle. I wasn't able to get out of the truck or walk myself to the door, so my son had to help me. When I got home, I took some Excedrin or Tylenol, but after a bit, I ended up throwing up. I was in my bed and I was so dizzy that I couldn't get up, so I threw up on my feet and the floor. The next morning, I woke up and felt like I had the flu. I threw up several times over the weekend. Come Monday, 05/10/2021, I asked my son if he could pick up some Pepto bismol because it helped a bit. On Monday evening, my son bought me a humidifier because we thought that maybe it was a sinus infection. On Wednesday, 05/12, I had to take an Uber to the hospital. While I was at the hospital, I had an MRI, a CT scan and blood work drawn. At first, they thought there was a blood clot in my lungs, but then it was ruled out. They gave me Benadryl and something else (he called it a cocktail). It took away some of the pain, but the headache never went away. They kept me overnight for observation and to do a second MRI in the morning. I was on a heart monitor the whole time. I saw a doctor before I left, and they weren't able to locate any problems. They came up with migraines. I was given a shot of sumatriptan and the same medicine in pill form 100mg to take when I was at home. As of today, 3 months after receiving my vaccine, I am still feeling foggy, and I have had quite a few headaches. I ended up seeing a Neurologist. With the medicine she gave me, I have not been feeling like myself at all. I stopped taking the medicine on 07/08/2021.
LAB_DATA: I had 2 MRI's, a CT scan and bloodwork completed.
OTHER_MEDS: I was taking Lisinopril, Zyrtec, albuterol inhaler,  fluticasone propionate nasal spray; multivitamin; Benadryl; melatonin gummies
CUR_ILL: I did not have any illness
HISTORY: I do have back and neck problems since my car accident
ALLERGIES: I do not have any allergies

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 4/5/21: Felt first symptoms while sitting in class. Felt very faint when I had to go to the bathroom and was better after I had gone. The following weeks after the first dose and before the second dose I would still get random faintness feelings and trouble breathing that would make me miss class, events, and other activities.  4/29/21: Received the second dose of Moderna Every day after the second vaccine I felt horribly faint even when I was completely hydrated. I could barely move and felt worse when I would stand or sit. At this point, I developed horrible fatigue and tiredness and even more problems with breathing. 5/13/21: Went to ER for horrible chest pain, heart palpitations, and feeling faint. An EKG, chest XRay, and blood work was completed which all came back normal. 5/16/21: Felt the worst I have ever felt. Was bed ridden for a week because I could not stand or do anything without feeling like passing out. Trouble breathing would get worse especially at night when I was going to bed. I would stop breathing when falling asleep and wake up gasping for air. 6/2/21: Developed a racing heart beat and my body would go into physical panics multiple times a day 6/4/21: Went to ER and had 15 tests done which all came back normal or negative 6/8/21: Visited primary doctor with same symptoms. Had a heart rate there of 110 while sitting and was prescribed a heart ultrasound and holter monitor for my heart 6/11/21: Experienced horrible night where I woke up feeling like my body was failing me and had horrible breathing issues. Went and got the heart ultrasound ad holter monitor put on which came back normal 6/22/21: Went back to primary doctor and had more tests completed since I was very weak, tired, and still felt faint. Came back positive for developing mono along with my other symptoms 6/23/21: Went to cardiologist where I was cleared for a good heart 7/13/21: Visited Gastroenterologist for stool issues that I noticed changed since the vaccine. Experiencing loose stools that are orange since the vaccine in April and now have a nerve triggered my body to make me feel faint whenever I go to bathroom. A colonoscopy is scheduled to make sure nothing else is going on. Overall, I have developed many adverse events that have left me incapable of doing anything. I cannot get a job because I feel awful still and would not be able to withstand a workday. It has also given me horrible anxiety that I NEVER had before that coincidentally appeared when I got the shot and hasn?t left. I still feel these symptoms mentioned above.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Client received her 2nd dose Pfizer COVID vaccine this afternoon at our offsite clinic by a LPN. Had just asked for a bandaid because there was a spot of blood where she had received the vaccine. Her sister reports she said she was feeling dizzy then her sister turned away and the client fell from standing position to the ground at 1412. Hit on her right side, shoulder and face. Lost conscious momentarily and together with family members we rolled her onto her back. I directed co-worker to call 911. Client came to and we helped her to sit up against the wall. Blood pressure 96/52, P 80 at 1415. Family and client denied history of seizures or fainting. Weather outside hot and client reported she hadn't eaten anything all day. Water provided. Client reported pain from the right side of her face and her lower lip which had a laceration from the fall that was bleeding a small amount. Fire EMS arrived just after 1420. Reported their vitals as BP 110/68, P 97, O2 99%. Ambulance arrived around 1430 and assessed. They had her rise from sitting to standing and reported her SBP dropped to the 70s. Paramedics advised to be assessed in ER. Client left in ambulance at 1443 accompanied by mother. Family provided reassurance regarding syncopal episode and contributing factors. They had no further questions or concerns at time of departure.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I sat in a chair for 15 minutes after getting my vaccine. One minute after sitting down, I had a headache, and I never get headaches. The headache got worse and worse. I had lunch, and I still had the headache afterwards. I then went home, and the headache got even worse. At about 2 AM, I got out of bed and tapped my head in the hope that it would help the headache and it  didn't. I then started to get a fever. The following morning, I had a full-blown fever, and I still had a horrific headache. I ended up having the headache for a whole week. With my fever, the temperature was 102; I didn't take anything, because I thought it would run its course and allow my body to get used to the vaccine. I eventually took two acetaminophen tablets, and it only reduced the temperature by one degree. I then took Advil, which also reduced it by one degree. The day after that, I had hives all over from the knees up, even in my crotch, eyes, and ears! I called a doctor, who prescribed me heavy-duty steroids. I was on steroids for 6 days . On the 4th day, I began to show signs of improvement. On the 9th day, the hives started to clear up, the headache began to subside, and the fever was gone. I had terrible fatigue for a while afterwards. Now, I'm trouble breathing. I always feel winded whenever I do any activity. Before the vaccine, I was very high-energy and had no trouble with fatigue or windedness.
LAB_DATA: None.
OTHER_MEDS: Activated You morning complete green drink.

Pt. started coughing Tuesday, June 22, 2021, in the afternoon and it worsened through the rest of day. She also was beginning to be drowsy. Wednesday, June 23, 2021, coughing continued, she became drowsier, she felt warm to the touch (forehead, face, arms, back) and was not acting like herself. Thursday, June 24, 2021, 9am she was at the clinic. The doctor ordered an x-ray and blood work. After results arrived, we were advised to go to the emergency room. There the doctor ordered CT scan. The results showed an abscess and fluid in her left lung and pneumonia. Her lung was drained, was not able to get all of it out. They discussed surgery but needed to send pt. to ER. The discussion for surgery was a daily thing but never happened. They tried multiple procedures, CT scans, etc. On Tuesday, June 29, 2021 there was a meeting called with her doctor to discuss palliative care. The risk of surgery and all the complications following were high risk. Pt. did not understand that she needed to leave the IV and drainage tube in as well as leaving the oxygen on. Based on the complications and pts. quality of life after surgery and the fact that the fluid and pneumonia spread quickly throughout her body - the doctors were leaning towards end-of-life comfort. It all happened so fast! The evening of the 29th, pt. was transported home to end her life on hospice. On Wednesday, June 30, 2021 pt. passed away in the afternoon. Pt. was rarely ever sick. Once in a great while she would get a runny nose or little cough. Everyone around her would catch a virus and she simply would not. We had a member of our family test positive for COVID-19 in November 2020, and pt. never showed any symptoms of being ill.  This was all before she received the COVID-19 Vaccine. About a week or two after she received the second vaccine, on May 27,2021. she had increased behaviors with eating and daily ADLs. But the behaviors were her ?normal? behaviors that would occasionally come and go. Nothing was ever persistent.  Then on Tuesday June 22, 2021 when sick like symptoms started to appear it was less then four weeks after the second vaccine.
OTHER_MEDS: Divalproex, Vyvanse, Risperidone, multivitamin, vitamin D3
HISTORY: ADHD, Epilepsy, Anxiety, Microcephalus, Autism, urinary incontinence, incontinence of feces

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient had a vagal response caused by an anxiety attack due to fear of needles. Technician, gave the vaccine and then immediately called me in. The mother and son were worried about the needle disappearing due to the retraction mechanism. The son was loosing color in his face and becoming dizzy. I had him sit upright, talked with him for a few minutes, gave him Benadryl as a precaution, and checked his blood pressure. He was having no difficulty breathing and blood pressure was WNL. His mother said that he has passed out with needles before and that he had not eaten today. Eventually the patient claimed to lose his sight, and within 30s passed out. He was still sitting in the chair, bent over, vomited, and then immediately came back to consciousness. The patient then said that he felt fine and wanted to leave. I talked with him and his mother for around 20 minutes, had him eat a banana, and drink a full bottle of water. After the time, he felt fine and him and his mother left.
PRIOR_VAX: Mother claimed he typically has a fear of needles and sometimes passes out with vaccines or blood draws.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Early in the morning Saturday, the day after the injection, patient became very nauseaus with a bad headache.  She was sick all day on Saturday with nausea and headache.  She could not sleep.  On Sunday, she felt worse and called ambulance.  They came and checked her out.  Said Oxygen level was normal and all her symptoms were normal side effects.  They did not take her to the hospital.  All day Sunday, she continued to be agitated and not able to get comfortable.  She was hot and cold, back and forth.  Her headache was very bad and she felt like she would throw up, but only threw up a little that day.  By Monday, she started not making sense and slurred her words.  We thought this was due to lack of sleep (exhaustion).  Her sugar was high, so we gave her an insulin shot.  She continued to make less and less sense so we called 911 approximately 7 PM on Monday night.  She was hallucinating.  At the hospital, they looked for infection, but could not find any source of infection.  They intubated her and soon after this, her heart stopped breathing.  They performed CPR 3 times, but not successful.  She died at 5 AM Tuesday morning.
LAB_DATA: ER did lab work and x-rays to try to find source of problem - they were unsuccessful

Uveitis on left eye causing extreme pain. Prednisolone Acetate (hourly) and Atropine were prescribed. A periocular corticosteroid injection was done less than a week later and medication stopped. Within 48 hours the uveitis flared and I was back to hourly Prednisolone. I was gradually weened off weekly for the subsequent four weeks. Then synechiae formed 360 degrees around the iris, causing iris bombe and pressure topping out at 63. An emergency laser peripheral iridotomy was performed creating a hole in the iris; Diamox 250 and Combigan were prescribed (3/day & 2/day respectively) in conjunction with Prednisolone (4/day). Two days later with the pressure again elevated, we attempted to break the synechiae via dilation (Diamox stopped). This process was repeated two more times in the following two weeks. Within this time frame, pressure escalated to 45 and I was put back on Diamox (4/day) and Latanoprost was prescribed (1/day). Also Tropicamide 1% and Phenylephrine 2.5% were prescribed (3/day each) to attempt to keep eye dilated. With the dilation not working, the hole completely sealed due to inflammation and the bombae yet again returning, another iridotomy was done. This time reopening the original and producing two additional holes. Currently I am off Diamox, Latanoprost, Tropicamide and Phenylephrine - but still on Atopine (3/day), Combigan (2/day) and Prednisolone Acetate (hourly). One day after the second laser, my pressure is currently at 6 with mild inflammation. I have another appointment with both Dr's on 7/19 to see if it will hold without the Diamox.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: So April 23rd during the day I felt a weird numbness in my tongue on the right side. I thought that maybe I burned it or bit it or something similar.  Then I went to work that night because I worked over nights(it was a very stressful night).  About halfway through the night into the early morning may be about 3:00 a.m. I started to feel we are numbness on the right side of my face I cannot just chalked it up to stress. When I left in the morning if I like it wasn't really moving right, just felt a little off. It was about 7:00 a.m. At this point I still thought I was just overly stressed I told my husband when I got home and just tried to lay down to relax. I had had  a slight ear ache for about 3 days but at this point it became more uncomfortable than it had been and my face felt like It was getting worse and it really started to worry me. So I decided to go to the walk in at Medical group. I saw the nurse practitioner.  At this point my face wasn't doing everything it was supposed to be doing but it wasn't fully numb yet. She said it could be due to an ear infection so she checked my ears but she said that it was weird because it was just slightly red. She wanted to transfer me over to the emergency Room is so that I could get a cat scan done. The doctor at the ER said that she wouldn't do a cat scan at this point she would just treat the ear infection so there was no point in moving me over to the ER. So the nurse practitioner prescribed a couple different medications and suggested that I follow up as soon as possible with my primary. Throughout the rest the day on April 24th ,when I saw the nurse practitioner, my face got progressively worse and wasn't moving very much closer to the end of the night. By the next day my right side of my face was not moving at all and that was April 25th. April 26th As soon as possible in the morning I called my primary care doctor and they got me in immediately to see her. She was unsure it was due to the ear infection and wanted to get more tests done to make sure that something else wasn't causing it and it could get worse. In at this point there was pain slightly so I  had taken some time off from work to get the test done.   The tests were an MRI scan and some blood work.  Then I had a follow up appointment with her right after. With in a couple days after first seeing my primary I had so much pain that I couldn't even get out of bed. It hurt to even slightly touch that side of my face or neck.  They said with it being nerve pain there wasn't much that they could give me or do to get that would help it go away. I ended up having about 2 weeks off from work before I went back not sure if I was fully ready with of the pain that I was having in my face still was not working but I could not afford not to. All the medication and everything that I was on during  the 1st 2 weeks had caused my palpitations to act up so I ended up having to get more tests on top of it to make sure that it was not negatively affecting my heart.  It's been over 2 months closer to almost 3 months and my face is now slightly working not all the way though but it is getting there. so not fully recovered. and having to watch my heart rate and thyroid levels (since i had been having good levels for two years she was worried it would make it act up or  cause a problem with the nodules i have on thyroid. ) hopefully I haven't missed any information. Just hoping there is no perminent damage or side effects and that after some more time it fully goes away.
LAB_DATA: Creatinine  blood draw, MRI of brain with and without contrast, X-ray, EKG, Holter monitor, Echocardiogram,  TSH blood draw,  Nothing showed significant findings to what caused it or anything very helpful. The MRI scan showed the abnormal enhancement of the right facial nerve that is consistent with bell's palsy. so conclusion was bell's palsy with unsure cause possibly ear infection.  Follow up more on thyroid I needed to have an ultrasound of thyroid which did show a growth in one of the nodules which then lead to a thyroid asperation of the nodule waiting to hear back for the last one.  hopefully I haven't missed any information
HISTORY: graves disease, palpitations, asthma, allergies, pcos, chronic heartburn, vitamin d deficiency,   depression, anxiety,
